{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KvZMxiUrPVYdfSAqgi1AnM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     3→   <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     4→   <groupId>io.openliberty.samples</groupId>\n     5→   <artifactId>io.openliberty.sample.daytrader8</artifactId>\n     6→   <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n     7→   <packaging>war</packaging>\n     8→   <properties>\n     9→      <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    10→      <project.reporting.outputEncoding>UTF-8</project.reporting.outputEncoding>\n    11→      <maven.compiler.source>1.8</maven.compiler.source>\n    12→      <maven.compiler.target>1.8</maven.compiler.target>\n    13→      <!-- Liberty configuration -->\n    14→      <testServerHttpPort>9080</testServerHttpPort>\n    15→      <testServerHttpsPort>9443</testServerHttpsPort>\n    16→   </properties>\n    17→   <dependencies>\n    18→      <dependency>\n    19→         <groupId>javax</groupId>\n    20→         <artifactId>javaee-api</artifactId>\n    21→         <version>8.0</version>\n    22→         <scope>provided</scope>\n    23→      </dependency>\n    24→      <!-- <dependency>\n    25→         <groupId>taglibs</groupId>\n    26→         <artifactId>standard</artifactId>\n    27→         <version>1.1.1</version>\n    28→         <scope>compile</scope>\n    29→      </dependency> -->\n    30→      <dependency>\n    31→         <groupId>org.apache.taglibs</groupId>\n    32→         <artifactId>taglibs-standard-spec</artifactId>\n    33→         <version>1.2.5</version>\n    34→      </dependency>\n    35→      <dependency>\n    36→         <groupId>org.apache.taglibs</groupId>\n    37→         <artifactId>taglibs-standard-impl</artifactId>\n    38→         <version>1.2.5</version>\n    39→      </dependency>\n    40→\n    41→\n    42→      <dependency>\n    43→         <groupId>javax.xml.bind</groupId>\n    44→         <artifactId>jaxb-api</artifactId>\n    45→         <version>2.3.0</version>\n    46→         <scope>provided</scope>\n    47→      </dependency>\n    48→      <dependency>\n    49→         <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    50→         <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    51→         <version>2.3.232</version>\n    52→         <scope>test</scope>\n    53→      </dependency>\n    54→   </dependencies>\n    55→   <build>\n    56→      <finalName>${project.artifactId}</finalName>\n    57→      <!-- Enable liberty-maven plugin -->\n    58→      <plugins>\n    59→         <plugin>\n    60→            <groupId>io.openliberty.tools</groupId>\n    61→            <artifactId>liberty-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    62→            <version>3.3-M4</version>\n    63→            <configuration>\n    64→              <bootstrapProperties>\n    65→                <default.http.port>${testServerHttpPort}</default.http.port>\n    66→                <default.https.port>${testServerHttpsPort}</default.https.port>\n    67→              </bootstrapProperties>\n    68→               <copyDependencies>\n    69→                  <dependencyGroup>\n    70→                  <location>${project.build.directory}/liberty/wlp/usr/shared/resources</location>\n    71→                  <dependency>\n    72→                     <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    73→                     <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    74→                     <version>2.3.232</version>\n    75→                  </dependency>\n    76→                  </dependencyGroup>\n    77→               </copyDependencies>\n    78→            </configuration>\n    79→         </plugin>\n    80→         <plugin>\n    81→            <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    82→            <artifactId>maven-dependency-plugin</artifactId>\n    83→            <version>3.1.2</version>\n    84→         </plugin>\n    85→         <plugin>\n    86→            <artifactId>maven-resources-plugin</artifactId>\n    87→            <version>2.6</version>\n    88→            <executions>\n    89→               <execution>\n    90→                  <id>copy-resources</id>\n    91→                  <phase>package</phase>\n    92→                  <goals>\n    93→                     <goal>copy-resources</goal>\n    94→                  </goals>\n    95→                  <configuration>\n    96→                     <outputDirectory>${project.build.directory}/liberty/wlp/usr/shared/resources/data</outputDirectory>\n    97→                     <resources>\n    98→                        <resource>\n    99→                           <directory>resources/data</directory>\n   100→                           <filtering>false</filtering>\n   101→                        </resource>\n   102→                     </resources>\n   103→                  </configuration>\n   104→               </execution>\n   105→            </executions>\n   106→         </plugin>\n   107→      </plugins>\n   108→   </build>\n   109→</project>\n   110→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"092ec3fa-8fbf-48ee-9ca2-ef10dee3c444"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QpD7XoGECGDYyNqFn95rir","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"liberty:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"1e018edc-5dd2-4d41-918f-6fb1bccd2e03"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JNiNoau23vwFn9oj6A3zhJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server>\n     3→   <featureManager>\n     4→      <feature>ejb-3.2</feature>\n     5→      <feature>servlet-4.0</feature>\n     6→      <feature>jsf-2.3</feature>\n     7→      <feature>jpa-2.2</feature>\n     8→      <feature>mdb-3.2</feature>\n     9→      <feature>wasJmsServer-1.0</feature>\n    10→      <feature>wasJmsClient-2.0</feature>\n    11→      <feature>cdi-2.0</feature>\n    12→      <feature>websocket-1.1</feature>\n    13→      <feature>concurrent-1.0</feature>\n    14→      <feature>jsonp-1.1</feature>\n    15→      <feature>jsonb-1.0</feature>\n    16→      <feature>beanValidation-2.0</feature>\n    17→      <feature>jaxrs-2.1</feature>\n    18→      <feature>ssl-1.0</feature>\n    19→   </featureManager>\n    20→\n    21→   <keyStore id=\"defaultKeyStore\" password=\"yourPassword\" />\n    22→\n    23→   <!--<logging traceSpecification=\"daytrader=fine\"/>-->\n    24→\n    25→   <!-- allow reuse of 'busy' ports for fast server recycling on linux (where ports remain blocked for up to 2 mins after server stops) ${tradelite.http.port} set in bootstrap.properties -->\n    26→   <httpEndpoint host=\"*\" httpPort=\"${default.http.port}\" httpsPort=\"${default.https.port}\" id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\">\n    27→      <tcpOptions soReuseAddr=\"true\" />\n    28→      <httpOptions maxKeepAliveRequests=\"-1\" />\n    29→   </httpEndpoint>\n    30→  \n    31→   <application location=\"io.openliberty.sample.daytrader8.war\" type=\"war\" context-root=\"/daytrader\" />\n    32→   \n    33→   <library id=\"h2Library\">\n    34→      <fileset dir=\"${shared.resource.dir}\" includes=\"h2*.jar\"/>\n    35→   </library>\n    36→\n    37→   <authData id=\"TradeDataSourceAuthData\" password=\"db_password\" user=\"db_username\" />\n    38→   <authData id=\"TradeAdminAuthData\" password=\"db_password\" user=\"db_username\" />\n    39→\n    40→   <connectionManager agedTimeout=\"-1\" connectionTimeout=\"0\" id=\"conMgr1\" maxIdleTime=\"-1\" maxPoolSize=\"100\" minPoolSize=\"100\" purgePolicy=\"FailingConnectionOnly\" reapTime=\"-1\" />  \n    41→   <dataSource connectionManagerRef=\"conMgr1\" id=\"DefaultDataSource\" isolationLevel=\"TRANSACTION_READ_COMMITTED\"  jndiName=\"jdbc/TradeDataSource\" statementCacheSize=\"60\">\n    42→      <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Library\" />\n    43→      <properties URL=\"jdbc:h2:file:${shared.resource.dir}/data/tradedb\" password=\"db_password\" user=\"db_username\" />\n    44→   </dataSource>\n    45→   \n    46→   <messagingEngine id=\"defaultME\">\n    47→      <queue id=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" />\n    48→      <topicSpace id=\"TradeTopicSpace\" />\n    49→   </messagingEngine>\n    50→   \n    51→   <connectionManager id=\"ConMgr2\" maxPoolSize=\"20\" />\n    52→   <jmsQueueConnectionFactory connectionManagerRef=\"ConMgr2\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeBrokerQCF\">\n    53→      <properties.wasJms />\n    54→   </jmsQueueConnectionFactory>\n    55→   \n    56→   <connectionManager id=\"ConMgr3\" maxPoolSize=\"20\" />\n    57→   <jmsTopicConnectionFactory connectionManagerRef=\"ConMgr3\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeStreamerTCF\">\n    58→      <properties.wasJms />\n    59→   </jmsTopicConnectionFactory> \n    60→   \n    61→   <jmsQueue id=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeBrokerQueue\">\n    62→      <properties.wasJms deliveryMode=\"NonPersistent\" queueName=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" />\n    63→   </jmsQueue>\n    64→   \n    65→   <jmsTopic id=\"TradeStreamerTopic\" jndiName=\"jms/TradeStreamerTopic\">\n    66→      <properties.wasJms deliveryMode=\"NonPersistent\" topicSpace=\"TradeTopicSpace\" />\n    67→   </jmsTopic>\n    68→  \n    69→  <jmsActivationSpec id=\"io.openliberty.sample.daytrader8/DTBroker3MDB\">\n    70→      <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"TradeBrokerQueue\" />\n    71→   </jmsActivationSpec>\n    72→   \n    73→   <jmsActivationSpec id=\"io.openliberty.sample.daytrader8/DTStreamer3MDB\">\n    74→      <properties.wasJms destinationRef=\"TradeStreamerTopic\" destinationType=\"javax.jms.Topic\" />\n    75→   </jmsActivationSpec>\n    76→</server>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"0d2157c7-6380-4d12-8961-498e3aaf5b8b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0131s9xH3zh4R8zQo3aKHNFq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!-- \n     3→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     4→ *\n     5→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     6→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     7→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     8→ *\n     9→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n    10→ *\n    11→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    12→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    13→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    14→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    15→ * limitations under the License.\n    16→-->\n    17→<web-app xmlns=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee\"\n    18→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n    19→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee/web-app_4_0.xsd\"\n    20→         version=\"4.0\">\n    21→    <display-name>DayTrader Web</display-name>\n    22→    <context-param>\n    23→        <param-name>javax.faces.PROJECT_STAGE</param-name>\n    24→        <param-value>Production</param-value>\n    25→    </context-param>\n    26→    <context-param>\n    27→        <param-name>javax.faces.STATE_SAVING_METHOD</param-name>\n    28→        <param-value>server</param-value>\n    29→    </context-param>\n    30→    <context-param>\n    31→        <param-name>javax.faces.DEFAULT_SUFFIX</param-name>\n    32→        <param-value>.xhtml</param-value>\n    33→    </context-param>\n    34→           \n    35→    <servlet>\n    36→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    37→        <servlet-class>javax.faces.webapp.FacesServlet</servlet-class>\n    38→        <load-on-startup>0</load-on-startup>\n    39→        <enabled>true</enabled>\n    40→        <async-supported>false</async-supported>\n    41→    </servlet>\n    42→\n    43→    <servlet-mapping>\n    44→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    45→        <url-pattern>*.faces</url-pattern>\n    46→    </servlet-mapping>\n    47→\n    48→    <session-config>\n    49→        <session-timeout>30</session-timeout>\n    50→    </session-config>\n    51→    \n    52→    <welcome-file-list>\n    53→    \t<welcome-file>index.html</welcome-file>\n    54→    \t<welcome-file>index.jsp</welcome-file>\n    55→    \t<welcome-file>index.faces</welcome-file>\n    56→    </welcome-file-list>\n    57→\n    58→    <error-page>\n    59→        <exception-type>java.lang.Exception</exception-type>\n    60→        <location>/error.jsp</location>\n    61→    </error-page>\n    62→\n    63→    <error-page>\n    64→        <error-code>500</error-code>\n    65→        <location>/error.jsp</location>\n    66→    </error-page>\n    67→      \n    68→    <!-- BASIC SECURITY ROLES AND CONSTRAINTS \n    69→\n    70→    <security-role>\n    71→\n    72→        <role-name>testing</role-name>\n    73→\n    74→    </security-role>\n    75→\n    76→\n    77→    <security-constraint>\n    78→\n    79→        <web-resource-collection>\n    80→\t\t\t<web-resource-name>testing</web-resource-name>\n    81→            <url-pattern>/*</url-pattern>\n    82→        </web-resource-collection>\n    83→\n    84→        <auth-constraint>\n    85→\n    86→            <role-name>testing</role-name>\n    87→\n    88→        </auth-constraint>\n    89→\n    90→    </security-constraint>\n    91→\n    92→\n    93→    <security-constraint>\n    94→        <display-name>\n    95→            Constraint1\n    96→        </display-name>\n    97→        <web-resource-collection>\n    98→            <web-resource-name>AllAuthd area</web-resource-name>\n    99→            <url-pattern>/*</url-pattern>\n   100→            <http-method>GET</http-method>\n   101→            <http-method>PUT</http-method>\n   102→            <http-method>POST</http-method>\n   103→            <http-method>DELETE</http-method>\n   104→        </web-resource-collection>\n   105→        <auth-constraint>\n   106→            <description>\n   107→            </description>\n   108→            <role-name>AllAuthenticated</role-name>\n   109→        </auth-constraint>\n   110→    </security-constraint>\n   111→    <security-constraint>\n   112→        <display-name>\n   113→            Constraint2\n   114→        </display-name>\n   115→        <web-resource-collection>\n   116→            <web-resource-name>Protected Area</web-resource-name>\n   117→            <url-pattern>/daytrader/servlet/PingServlet2Session2Entity/*\n   118→            </url-pattern>\n   119→            <url-pattern>/servlet/PingServlet2Session2Entity/*\n   120→            </url-pattern>\n   121→            <url-pattern>/PingServlet2Session2Entity/*</url-pattern>\n   122→            <url-pattern>/PingServlet2Session2Entity</url-pattern>\n   123→            <http-method>GET</http-method>\n   124→            <http-method>PUT</http-method>\n   125→            <http-method>POST</http-method>\n   126→            <http-method>DELETE</http-method>\n   127→        </web-resource-collection>\n   128→        <web-resource-collection>\n   129→            <web-resource-name>Protected Area 2</web-resource-name>\n   130→            <url-pattern>/daytrader/servlet/TradeScenarioServlet/*\n   131→            </url-pattern>\n   132→            <url-pattern>/servlet/TradeScenarioServlet/*</url-pattern>\n   133→            <url-pattern>/TradeScenarioServlet/*</url-pattern>\n   134→            <url-pattern>TradeScenarioServlet</url-pattern>\n   135→            <http-method>GET</http-method>\n   136→            <http-method>PUT</http-method>\n   137→            <http-method>POST</http-method>\n   138→            <http-method>DELETE</http-method>\n   139→        </web-resource-collection>\n   140→        <web-resource-collection>\n   141→            <web-resource-name>Protected Area 3</web-resource-name>\n   142→            <url-pattern>/daytrader/servlet/TradeAppServlet/*\n   143→            </url-pattern>\n   144→            <url-pattern>/servlet/TradeAppServlet/*</url-pattern>\n   145→            <url-pattern>/TradeAppServlet/*</url-pattern>\n   146→            <url-pattern>/daytrader/app/*</url-pattern>\n   147→            <url-pattern>/daytrader/app</url-pattern>\n   148→            <url-pattern>/daytrader/*</url-pattern>\n   149→            <url-pattern>/app</url-pattern>\n   150→            <url-pattern>/*</url-pattern>\n   151→            <http-method>GET</http-method>\n   152→            <http-method>PUT</http-method>\n   153→            <http-method>POST</http-method>\n   154→            <http-method>DELETE</http-method>\n   155→        </web-resource-collection>\n   156→        <auth-constraint>\n   157→            <description>\n   158→            </description>\n   159→            <role-name>grp1</role-name>\n   160→            <role-name>grp2</role-name>\n   161→            <role-name>grp3</role-name>\n   162→            <role-name>grp4</role-name>\n   163→            <role-name>grp5</role-name>\n   164→            <role-name>webSecOnly</role-name>\n   165→        </auth-constraint>\n   166→    </security-constraint>\n   167→    <security-role>\n   168→        <description>\n   169→            All Authenticated Users\n   170→        </description>\n   171→        <role-name>AllAuthenticated</role-name>\n   172→    </security-role>\n   173→    <security-role>\n   174→        <description>\n   175→            Group 1\n   176→        </description>\n   177→        <role-name>grp1</role-name>\n   178→    </security-role>\n   179→    <security-role>\n   180→        <description>\n   181→            Group 2\n   182→        </description>\n   183→        <role-name>grp2</role-name>\n   184→    </security-role>\n   185→    <security-role>\n   186→        <description>\n   187→            Group 3\n   188→        </description>\n   189→        <role-name>grp3</role-name>\n   190→    </security-role>\n   191→    <security-role>\n   192→        <description>\n   193→            Group 4\n   194→        </description>\n   195→        <role-name>grp4</role-name>\n   196→    </security-role>\n   197→    <security-role>\n   198→        <description>\n   199→            Group 5\n   200→        </description>\n   201→        <role-name>grp5</role-name>\n   202→    </security-role>\n   203→    <security-role>\n   204→        <description>\n   205→            WebSecOnly\n   206→        </description>\n   207→        <role-name>webSecOnly</role-name>\n   208→    </security-role>\n   209→\n   210→    <login-config>\n   211→\n   212→        <auth-method>BASIC</auth-method>\n   213→\n   214→    </login-config>\t  -->   \n   215→</web-app>\n   216→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"2c0985f9-6fa2-4b98-b38c-26f18e37397a"}
