{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017qizwzyJbpmzX6qFVRRX8R","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→\n    29→/**\n    30→ * TradeServices interface specifies the business methods provided by the Trade\n    31→ * online broker application. These business methods represent the features and\n    32→ * operations that can be performed by customers of the brokerage such as login,\n    33→ * logout, get a stock quote, buy or sell a stock, etc. This interface is\n    34→ * implemented by {@link Trade} providing an EJB implementation of these\n    35→ * business methods and also by {@link TradeDirect} providing a JDBC\n    36→ * implementation.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * @see TradeDirect\n    39→ * @see TradeSLSB\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→\n    43→public interface TradeServices {\n    44→\n    45→    /**\n    46→     * Compute and return a snapshot of the current market conditions This\n    47→     * includes the TSIA - an index of the price of the top 100 Trade stock\n    48→     * quotes The openTSIA ( the index at the open) The volume of shares traded,\n    49→     * Top Stocks gain and loss\n    50→     *\n    51→     * @return A snapshot of the current market summary\n    52→     */\n    53→    MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception;\n    54→\n    55→    /**\n    56→     * Create an order (buy or sell)\n    57→     *\n    58→     * @param accoount\n    59→     *            the accountdatabean\n    60→     * @param quote\n    61→     *            the quptedatabean\n    62→     * @param holding\n    63→     *            the holdingdatabean\n    64→     * @param orderType\n    65→     *            buy or sell\n    66→     * @param quantity\n    67→     *            quantity            \n    68→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n    69→     */\n    70→    OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType,\n    71→        double quantity) throws Exception;\n    72→    \n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Purchase a stock and create a new holding for the given user. Given a\n    75→     * stock symbol and quantity to purchase, retrieve the current quote price,\n    76→     * debit the user's account balance, and add holdings to user's portfolio.\n    77→     * buy/sell are asynchronous, using J2EE messaging, A new order is created\n    78→     * and submitted for processing to the TradeBroker\n    79→     *\n    80→     * @param userID\n    81→     *            the customer requesting the stock purchase\n    82→     * @param symbol\n    83→     *            the symbol of the stock being purchased\n    84→     * @param quantity\n    85→     *            the quantity of shares to purchase\n    86→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created buy order\n    87→     */\n    88→\n    89→    OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n    90→\n    91→    /**\n    92→     * Sell a stock holding and removed the holding for the given user. Given a\n    93→     * Holding, retrieve current quote, credit user's account, and reduce\n    94→     * holdings in user's portfolio.\n    95→     *\n    96→     * @param userID\n    97→     *            the customer requesting the sell\n    98→     * @param holdingID\n    99→     *            the users holding to be sold\n   100→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created sell\n   101→     *         order\n   102→     */\n   103→    OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Queue the Order identified by orderID to be processed\n   107→     *\n   108→     * Orders are submitted through JMS to a Trading Broker and completed\n   109→     * asynchronously. This method queues the order for processing\n   110→     *\n   111→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   112→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   113→     *\n   114→     * @param orderID\n   115→     *            the Order being queued for processing\n   116→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   117→     */\n   118→    void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   119→\n   120→    /**\n   121→     * Complete the Order identified by orderID. This method completes\n   122→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   123→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   124→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   125→     *\n   126→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   127→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   128→     *\n   129→     * @param orderID\n   130→     *            the Order to complete\n   131→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   132→     */\n   133→    OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   134→\n   135→    /**\n   136→     * Complete the Order identefied by orderID Orders are completed \n   137→     * asynchronously. This method completes\n   138→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   139→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   140→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   141→     *\n   142→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   143→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @param orderID\n   146→     *            the Order to complete\n   147→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   148→     */\n   149→    Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   150→    \n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Cancel the Order identefied by orderID\n   153→     *\n   154→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   155→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   156→     *\n   157→     * @param orderID\n   158→     *            the Order to complete\n   159→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   160→     */\n   161→    void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   162→\n   163→    /**\n   164→     * Signify an order has been completed for the given userID\n   165→     *\n   166→     * @param userID\n   167→     *            the user for which an order has completed\n   168→     * @param orderID\n   169→     *            the order which has completed\n   170→     *\n   171→     */\n   172→    void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception;\n   173→\n   174→    /**\n   175→     * Get the collection of all orders for a given account\n   176→     *\n   177→     * @param userID\n   178→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   179→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   180→     */\n   181→    Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   182→\n   183→    /**\n   184→     * Get the collection of completed orders for a given account that need to\n   185→     * be alerted to the user\n   186→     *\n   187→     * @param userID\n   188→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   189→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   190→     */\n   191→    Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   192→\n   193→    /**\n   194→     * Given a market symbol, price, and details, create and return a new\n   195→     * {@link QuoteDataBean}\n   196→     *\n   197→     * @param symbol\n   198→     *            the symbol of the stock\n   199→     * @param price\n   200→     *            the current stock price\n   201→     * @param details\n   202→     *            a short description of the stock or company\n   203→     * @return a new QuoteDataBean or null if Quote could not be created\n   204→     */\n   205→    QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception;\n   206→\n   207→    /**\n   208→     * Return a {@link QuoteDataBean} describing a current quote for the given\n   209→     * stock symbol\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param symbol\n   212→     *            the stock symbol to retrieve the current Quote\n   213→     * @return the QuoteDataBean\n   214→     */\n   215→    QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   216→\n   217→    /**\n   218→     * Return a {@link java.util.Collection} of {@link QuoteDataBean} describing\n   219→     * all current quotes\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return A collection of QuoteDataBean\n   222→     */\n   223→    Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception;\n   224→\n   225→    /**\n   226→     * Update the stock quote price and volume for the specified stock symbol\n   227→     *\n   228→     * @param symbol\n   229→     *            for stock quote to update\n   230→     * @param price\n   231→     *            the updated quote price\n   232→     * @return the QuoteDataBean describing the stock\n   233→     */\n   234→    QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded) throws Exception;\n   235→\n   236→    /**\n   237→     * Return the portfolio of stock holdings for the specified customer as a\n   238→     * collection of HoldingDataBeans\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @param userID\n   241→     *            the customer requesting the portfolio\n   242→     * @return Collection of the users portfolio of stock holdings\n   243→     */\n   244→    Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception;\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Return a specific user stock holding identifed by the holdingID\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param holdingID\n   250→     *            the holdingID to return\n   251→     * @return a HoldingDataBean describing the holding\n   252→     */\n   253→    HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception;\n   254→\n   255→    /**\n   256→     * Return an AccountDataBean object for userID describing the account\n   257→     *\n   258→     * @param userID\n   259→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   260→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   261→     */\n   262→    AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   263→\n   264→    /**\n   265→     * Return an AccountProfileDataBean for userID providing the users profile\n   266→     *\n   267→     * @param userID\n   268→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   269→     * @param User\n   270→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   271→     */\n   272→    AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   273→\n   274→    /**\n   275→     * Update userID's account profile information using the provided\n   276→     * AccountProfileDataBean object\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @param userID\n   279→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   280→     * @param User\n   281→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   282→     */\n   283→    AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception;\n   284→\n   285→    /**\n   286→     * Attempt to authenticate and login a user with the given password\n   287→     *\n   288→     * @param userID\n   289→     *            the customer to login\n   290→     * @param password\n   291→     *            the password entered by the customer for authentication\n   292→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   293→     */\n   294→    AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception;\n   295→\n   296→    /**\n   297→     * Logout the given user\n   298→     *\n   299→     * @param userID\n   300→     *            the customer to logout\n   301→     * @return the login status\n   302→     */\n   303→\n   304→    void logout(String userID) throws Exception;\n   305→\n   306→    /**\n   307→     * Register a new Trade customer. Create a new user profile, user registry\n   308→     * entry, account with initial balance, and empty portfolio.\n   309→     *\n   310→     * @param userID\n   311→     *            the new customer to register\n   312→     * @param password\n   313→     *            the customers password\n   314→     * @param fullname\n   315→     *            the customers fullname\n   316→     * @param address\n   317→     *            the customers street address\n   318→     * @param email\n   319→     *            the customers email address\n   320→     * @param creditcard\n   321→     *            the customers creditcard number\n   322→     * @param initialBalance\n   323→     *            the amount to charge to the customers credit to open the\n   324→     *            account and set the initial balance\n   325→     * @return the userID if successful, null otherwise\n   326→     */\n   327→    AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance)\n   328→            throws Exception;\n   329→\n   330→    \n   331→    int getImpl();\n   332→\n   333→    QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   334→\n   335→    double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception;\n   336→\n   337→    void setInSession(boolean inSession);\n   338→}\n   339→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"38417552-d63f-4429-8282-93cb4c3fe278"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G4ijJBbVv6VZ87bnNTVvY4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.Date;\n    23→\n    24→import javax.ejb.EJBException;\n    25→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    26→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    27→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    28→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    29→import javax.persistence.GenerationType;\n    30→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    31→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    32→import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\n    33→import javax.persistence.OneToOne;\n    34→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    35→import javax.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    36→import javax.persistence.Temporal;\n    37→import javax.persistence.TemporalType;\n    38→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    39→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    40→import javax.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    41→import javax.validation.constraints.PositiveOrZero;\n    42→\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    45→\n    46→@Entity(name = \"accountejb\")\n    47→@Table(name = \"accountejb\")\n    48→public class AccountDataBean implements Serializable {\n    49→\n    50→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 8437841265136840545L;\n    51→\n    52→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    53→    @TableGenerator(name = \"accountIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"account\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    54→    @Id\n    55→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"accountIdGen\")\n    56→    @Column(name = \"ACCOUNTID\", nullable = false)\n    57→    private Integer accountID; /* accountID */\n    58→\n    59→    @NotNull\n    60→    @PositiveOrZero\n    61→    @Column(name = \"LOGINCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    62→    private int loginCount; /* loginCount */\n    63→\n    64→    @NotNull\n    65→    @PositiveOrZero\n    66→    @Column(name = \"LOGOUTCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    67→    private int logoutCount; /* logoutCount */\n    68→\n    69→    @Column(name = \"LASTLOGIN\")\n    70→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    71→    @PastOrPresent\n    72→    private Date lastLogin; /* lastLogin Date */\n    73→\n    74→    @Column(name = \"CREATIONDATE\")\n    75→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    76→    @PastOrPresent\n    77→    private Date creationDate; /* creationDate */\n    78→\n    79→    @Column(name = \"BALANCE\")\n    80→    private BigDecimal balance; /* balance */\n    81→\n    82→    @Column(name = \"OPENBALANCE\")\n    83→    private BigDecimal openBalance; /* open balance */\n    84→\n    85→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    86→    private Collection<OrderDataBean> orders;\n    87→\n    88→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    89→    private Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings;\n    90→\n    91→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    92→    @JoinColumn(name = \"PROFILE_USERID\")\n    93→    private AccountProfileDataBean profile;\n    94→\n    95→    /*\n    96→     * Accessor methods for relationship fields are only included for the\n    97→     * AccountProfile profileID\n    98→     */\n    99→    @Transient\n   100→    private String profileID;\n   101→\n   102→    public AccountDataBean() {\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    public AccountDataBean(Integer accountID, int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate, BigDecimal balance, BigDecimal openBalance,\n   106→            String profileID) {\n   107→        setAccountID(accountID);\n   108→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n   109→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n   110→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n   111→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n   112→        setBalance(balance);\n   113→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   114→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    public AccountDataBean(int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate, BigDecimal balance, BigDecimal openBalance, String profileID) {\n   118→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n   119→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n   120→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n   121→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n   122→        setBalance(balance);\n   123→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   124→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public static AccountDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   128→        return new AccountDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), // accountID\n   129→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // loginCount\n   130→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // logoutCount\n   131→                new java.util.Date(), // lastLogin\n   132→                new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), // creationDate\n   133→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // balance\n   134→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // openBalance\n   135→                TradeConfig.rndUserID() // profileID\n   136→        );\n   137→    }\n   138→\n   139→    @Override\n   140→    public String toString() {\n   141→        return \"\\n\\tAccount Data for account: \" + getAccountID() + \"\\n\\t\\t   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t  logoutCount:\" + getLogoutCount()\n   142→                + \"\\n\\t\\t    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"\\n\\t\\t creationDate:\" + getCreationDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t      balance:\" + getBalance()\n   143→                + \"\\n\\t\\t  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"\\n\\t\\t    profileID:\" + getProfileID();\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    public String toHTML() {\n   147→        return \"<BR>Account Data for account: <B>\" + getAccountID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  logoutCount:\"\n   148→                + getLogoutCount() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> creationDate:\" + getCreationDate() + \"</LI>\"\n   149→                + \"<LI>      balance:\" + getBalance() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    profileID:\" + getProfileID()\n   150→                + \"</LI>\";\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    public void print() {\n   154→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   155→    }\n   156→\n   157→    public Integer getAccountID() {\n   158→        return accountID;\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    public void setAccountID(Integer accountID) {\n   162→        this.accountID = accountID;\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    public int getLoginCount() {\n   166→        return loginCount;\n   167→    }\n   168→\n   169→    public void setLoginCount(int loginCount) {\n   170→        this.loginCount = loginCount;\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    public int getLogoutCount() {\n   174→        return logoutCount;\n   175→    }\n   176→\n   177→    public void setLogoutCount(int logoutCount) {\n   178→        this.logoutCount = logoutCount;\n   179→    }\n   180→\n   181→    public Date getLastLogin() {\n   182→        return lastLogin;\n   183→    }\n   184→\n   185→    public void setLastLogin(Date lastLogin) {\n   186→        this.lastLogin = lastLogin;\n   187→    }\n   188→\n   189→    public Date getCreationDate() {\n   190→        return creationDate;\n   191→    }\n   192→\n   193→    public void setCreationDate(Date creationDate) {\n   194→        this.creationDate = creationDate;\n   195→    }\n   196→\n   197→    public BigDecimal getBalance() {\n   198→        return balance;\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    public void setBalance(BigDecimal balance) {\n   202→        this.balance = balance;\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    public BigDecimal getOpenBalance() {\n   206→        return openBalance;\n   207→    }\n   208→\n   209→    public void setOpenBalance(BigDecimal openBalance) {\n   210→        this.openBalance = openBalance;\n   211→    }\n   212→\n   213→    public String getProfileID() {\n   214→        return profileID;\n   215→    }\n   216→\n   217→    public void setProfileID(String profileID) {\n   218→        this.profileID = profileID;\n   219→    }\n   220→\n   221→    /*\n   222→     * Disabled for D185273 public String getUserID() { return getProfileID(); }\n   223→     */\n   224→\n   225→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders() {\n   226→        return orders;\n   227→    }\n   228→\n   229→    public void setOrders(Collection<OrderDataBean> orders) {\n   230→        this.orders = orders;\n   231→    }\n   232→\n   233→    public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings() {\n   234→        return holdings;\n   235→    }\n   236→\n   237→    public void setHoldings(Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings) {\n   238→        this.holdings = holdings;\n   239→    }\n   240→\n   241→    public AccountProfileDataBean getProfile() {\n   242→        return profile;\n   243→    }\n   244→\n   245→    public void setProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profile) {\n   246→        this.profile = profile;\n   247→    }\n   248→\n   249→    public void login(String password) {\n   250→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = getProfile();\n   251→        if ((profile == null) || (profile.getPassword().equals(password) == false)) {\n   252→            String error = \"AccountBean:Login failure for account: \" + getAccountID()\n   253→                    + ((profile == null) ? \"null AccountProfile\" : \"\\n\\tIncorrect password-->\" + profile.getUserID() + \":\" + profile.getPassword());\n   254→            throw new EJBException(error);\n   255→        }\n   256→\n   257→        setLastLogin(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   258→        setLoginCount(getLoginCount() + 1);\n   259→    }\n   260→\n   261→    public void logout() {\n   262→        setLogoutCount(getLogoutCount() + 1);\n   263→    }\n   264→\n   265→    @Override\n   266→    public int hashCode() {\n   267→        int hash = 0;\n   268→        hash += (this.accountID != null ? this.accountID.hashCode() : 0);\n   269→        return hash;\n   270→    }\n   271→\n   272→    @Override\n   273→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   274→        \n   275→        if (!(object instanceof AccountDataBean)) {\n   276→            return false;\n   277→        }\n   278→        AccountDataBean other = (AccountDataBean) object;\n   279→\n   280→        if (this.accountID != other.accountID && (this.accountID == null || !this.accountID.equals(other.accountID))) {\n   281→            return false;\n   282→        }\n   283→\n   284→        return true;\n   285→    }\n   286→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"2f1fd81f-a39d-4ee0-8b31-b6ed4739c531"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Wce1Y9SZT4JRbsFEn1LzcP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→\n    21→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    22→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    23→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    24→import javax.persistence.NamedNativeQueries;\n    25→import javax.persistence.NamedNativeQuery;\n    26→import javax.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    27→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    28→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    29→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    30→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    31→import javax.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    32→\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    35→\n    36→@Entity(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    37→@Table(name = \"quoteejb\")\n    38→@NamedQueries({\n    39→        @NamedQuery(name = \"quoteejb.allQuotes\", query = \"SELECT q FROM quoteejb q\")})\n    40→@NamedNativeQueries({ @NamedNativeQuery(name = \"quoteejb.quoteForUpdate\", query = \"select * from quoteejb q where q.symbol=? for update\", resultClass = com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean.class) })\n    41→public class QuoteDataBean implements Serializable {\n    42→\n    43→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    44→\n    45→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1847932261895838791L;\n    46→\n    47→    @Id\n    48→    @NotNull\n    49→    @Column(name = \"SYMBOL\", nullable = false)\n    50→    private String symbol; /* symbol */\n    51→\n    52→    @Column(name = \"COMPANYNAME\")\n    53→    @NotBlank\n    54→    private String companyName; /* companyName */\n    55→\n    56→    @NotNull\n    57→    @Column(name = \"VOLUME\", nullable = false)\n    58→    private double volume; /* volume */\n    59→\n    60→    @Column(name = \"PRICE\")\n    61→    @Positive\n    62→    private BigDecimal price; /* price */\n    63→\n    64→    @Column(name = \"OPEN1\")\n    65→    @Positive\n    66→    private BigDecimal open1; /* open1 price */\n    67→\n    68→    @Column(name = \"LOW\")\n    69→    @Positive\n    70→    private BigDecimal low; /* low price */\n    71→\n    72→    @Column(name = \"HIGH\")\n    73→    @Positive\n    74→    private BigDecimal high; /* high price */\n    75→\n    76→    @NotNull\n    77→    @Column(name = \"CHANGE1\", nullable = false)\n    78→    private double change1; /* price change */\n    79→\n    80→    /* Accessor methods for relationship fields are not kept in the DataBean */\n    81→\n    82→    public QuoteDataBean() {\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol, String companyName, double volume, BigDecimal price, BigDecimal open, BigDecimal low, BigDecimal high, double change) {\n    86→        setSymbol(symbol);\n    87→        setCompanyName(companyName);\n    88→        setVolume(volume);\n    89→        setPrice(price);\n    90→        setOpen(open);\n    91→        setLow(low);\n    92→        setHigh(high);\n    93→        setChange(change);\n    94→    }\n    95→\n    96→    public static QuoteDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    97→        return new QuoteDataBean(TradeConfig.rndSymbol(), // symbol\n    98→                TradeConfig.rndSymbol() + \" Incorporated\", // Company Name\n    99→                TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000), // volume\n   100→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // price\n   101→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // open1\n   102→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // low\n   103→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // high\n   104→                TradeConfig.rndFloat(100000) // volume\n   105→        );\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    // Create a \"zero\" value quoteDataBean for the given symbol\n   109→    public QuoteDataBean(String symbol) {\n   110→        setSymbol(symbol);\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    @Override\n   114→    public String toString() {\n   115→        return \"\\n\\tQuote Data for: \" + getSymbol() + \"\\n\\t\\t companyName: \" + getCompanyName() + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume: \" + getVolume() + \"\\n\\t\\t       price: \"\n   116→                + getPrice() + \"\\n\\t\\t        open1: \" + getOpen() + \"\\n\\t\\t         low: \" + getLow() + \"\\n\\t\\t        high: \" + getHigh()\n   117→                + \"\\n\\t\\t      change1: \" + getChange();\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    public String toHTML() {\n   121→        return \"<BR>Quote Data for: \" + getSymbol() + \"<LI> companyName: \" + getCompanyName() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      volume: \" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\"\n   122→                + \"<LI>       price: \" + getPrice() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>        open1: \" + getOpen() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>         low: \" + getLow() + \"</LI>\"\n   123→                + \"<LI>        high: \" + getHigh() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      change1: \" + getChange() + \"</LI>\";\n   124→    }\n   125→\n   126→    public void print() {\n   127→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    public String getSymbol() {\n   131→        return symbol;\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n   135→        this.symbol = symbol;\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    public String getCompanyName() {\n   139→        return companyName;\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    public void setCompanyName(String companyName) {\n   143→        this.companyName = companyName;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n   147→        return price;\n   148→    }\n   149→\n   150→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   151→        this.price = price;\n   152→    }\n   153→\n   154→    public BigDecimal getOpen() {\n   155→        return open1;\n   156→    }\n   157→\n   158→    public void setOpen(BigDecimal open) {\n   159→        this.open1 = open;\n   160→    }\n   161→\n   162→    public BigDecimal getLow() {\n   163→        return low;\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    public void setLow(BigDecimal low) {\n   167→        this.low = low;\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    public BigDecimal getHigh() {\n   171→        return high;\n   172→    }\n   173→\n   174→    public void setHigh(BigDecimal high) {\n   175→        this.high = high;\n   176→    }\n   177→\n   178→    public double getChange() {\n   179→        return change1;\n   180→    }\n   181→\n   182→    public void setChange(double change) {\n   183→        this.change1 = change;\n   184→    }\n   185→\n   186→    public double getVolume() {\n   187→        return volume;\n   188→    }\n   189→\n   190→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   191→        this.volume = volume;\n   192→    }\n   193→\n   194→    @Override\n   195→    public int hashCode() {\n   196→        int hash = 0;\n   197→        hash += (this.symbol != null ? this.symbol.hashCode() : 0);\n   198→        return hash;\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    @Override\n   202→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   203→        \n   204→        if (!(object instanceof QuoteDataBean)) {\n   205→            return false;\n   206→        }\n   207→        QuoteDataBean other = (QuoteDataBean) object;\n   208→        if (this.symbol != other.symbol && (this.symbol == null || !this.symbol.equals(other.symbol))) {\n   209→            return false;\n   210→        }\n   211→        return true;\n   212→    }\n   213→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"fa194247-7a29-47ef-b564-7646546dc892"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011Pa5toG1zCXQgVi8oX8wNM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→//import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    21→import java.util.Date;\n    22→\n    23→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    24→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    25→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    26→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    27→import javax.persistence.GenerationType;\n    28→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    29→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    30→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    31→import javax.persistence.NamedQueries;\n    32→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    33→import javax.persistence.OneToOne;\n    34→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    35→import javax.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    36→import javax.persistence.Temporal;\n    37→import javax.persistence.TemporalType;\n    38→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    39→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    40→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    41→import javax.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    42→import javax.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    43→\n    44→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    45→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    46→\n    47→@Entity(name = \"orderejb\")\n    48→@Table(name = \"orderejb\")\n    49→@NamedQueries({\n    50→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderfee\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderFee = :orderfee\"),\n    51→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByCompletiondate\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.completionDate = :completiondate\"),\n    52→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrdertype\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderType = :ordertype\"),\n    53→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderstatus\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderStatus = :orderstatus\"),\n    54→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByPrice\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.price = :price\"),\n    55→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByQuantity\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.quantity = :quantity\"),\n    56→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOpendate\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.openDate = :opendate\"),\n    57→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByOrderid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderID = :orderid\"),\n    58→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByAccountAccountid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.account.accountID = :accountAccountid\"),\n    59→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByQuoteSymbol\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.quote.symbol = :quoteSymbol\"),\n    60→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.findByHoldingHoldingid\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.holding.holdingID = :holdingHoldingid\"),\n    61→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.closedOrders\", query = \"SELECT o FROM orderejb o WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID  = :userID\"),\n    62→        @NamedQuery(name = \"orderejb.completeClosedOrders\", query = \"UPDATE orderejb o SET o.orderStatus = 'completed' WHERE o.orderStatus = 'closed' AND o.account.profile.userID  = :userID\") })\n    63→public class OrderDataBean implements Serializable {\n    64→\n    65→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 120650490200739057L;\n    66→\n    67→    @Id\n    68→    @TableGenerator(name = \"orderIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"order\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    69→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"orderIdGen\")\n    70→    @Column(name = \"ORDERID\", nullable = false)\n    71→    private Integer orderID; /* orderID */\n    72→\n    73→    @Column(name = \"ORDERTYPE\")\n    74→    @NotBlank\n    75→    private String orderType; /* orderType (buy, sell, etc.) */\n    76→\n    77→    @Column(name = \"ORDERSTATUS\")\n    78→    @NotBlank\n    79→    private String orderStatus; /*\n    80→                                 * orderStatus (open, processing, completed,\n    81→                                 * closed, cancelled)\n    82→                                 */\n    83→\n    84→    @Column(name = \"OPENDATE\")\n    85→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    86→    @PastOrPresent\n    87→    private Date openDate; /* openDate (when the order was entered) */\n    88→\n    89→    @Column(name = \"COMPLETIONDATE\")\n    90→    @PastOrPresent\n    91→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    92→    private Date completionDate; /* completionDate */\n    93→\n    94→    @NotNull\n    95→    @Column(name = \"QUANTITY\", nullable = false)\n    96→    private double quantity; /* quantity */\n    97→\n    98→    @Column(name = \"PRICE\")\n    99→    @Positive\n   100→    private BigDecimal price; /* price */\n   101→\n   102→    @Column(name = \"ORDERFEE\")\n   103→    @Positive\n   104→    private BigDecimal orderFee; /* price */\n   105→\n   106→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n   107→    @JoinColumn(name = \"ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID\")\n   108→    private AccountDataBean account;\n   109→\n   110→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n   111→    @JoinColumn(name = \"QUOTE_SYMBOL\")\n   112→    private QuoteDataBean quote;\n   113→\n   114→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n   115→    @JoinColumn(name = \"HOLDING_HOLDINGID\")\n   116→    private HoldingDataBean holding;\n   117→\n   118→    /* Fields for relationship fields are not kept in the Data Bean */\n   119→    @Transient\n   120→    private String symbol;\n   121→\n   122→    public OrderDataBean() {\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    public OrderDataBean(Integer orderID, String orderType, String orderStatus, Date openDate, Date completionDate, double quantity, BigDecimal price,\n   126→            BigDecimal orderFee, String symbol) {\n   127→        setOrderID(orderID);\n   128→        setOrderType(orderType);\n   129→        setOrderStatus(orderStatus);\n   130→        setOpenDate(openDate);\n   131→        setCompletionDate(completionDate);\n   132→        setQuantity(quantity);\n   133→        setPrice(price);\n   134→        setOrderFee(orderFee);\n   135→        setSymbol(symbol);\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    public OrderDataBean(String orderType, String orderStatus, Date openDate, Date completionDate, double quantity, BigDecimal price, BigDecimal orderFee,\n   139→            AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding) {\n   140→        setOrderType(orderType);\n   141→        setOrderStatus(orderStatus);\n   142→        setOpenDate(openDate);\n   143→        setCompletionDate(completionDate);\n   144→        setQuantity(quantity);\n   145→        setPrice(price);\n   146→        setOrderFee(orderFee);\n   147→        setAccount(account);\n   148→        setQuote(quote);\n   149→        setHolding(holding);\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public static OrderDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   153→        return new OrderDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), TradeConfig.rndBoolean() ? \"buy\" : \"sell\", \"open\", new java.util.Date(\n   154→                TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), TradeConfig.rndQuantity(),\n   155→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), TradeConfig.rndSymbol());\n   156→    }\n   157→\n   158→    @Override\n   159→    public String toString() {\n   160→        return \"Order \" + getOrderID() + \"\\n\\t      orderType: \" + getOrderType() + \"\\n\\t    orderStatus: \" + getOrderStatus() + \"\\n\\t       openDate: \"\n   161→                + getOpenDate() + \"\\n\\t completionDate: \" + getCompletionDate() + \"\\n\\t       quantity: \" + getQuantity() + \"\\n\\t          price: \"\n   162→                + getPrice() + \"\\n\\t       orderFee: \" + getOrderFee() + \"\\n\\t         symbol: \" + getSymbol();\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    public String toHTML() {\n   166→        return \"<BR>Order <B>\" + getOrderID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>      orderType: \" + getOrderType() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    orderStatus: \" + getOrderStatus()\n   167→                + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>       openDate: \" + getOpenDate() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> completionDate: \" + getCompletionDate() + \"</LI>\"\n   168→                + \"<LI>       quantity: \" + getQuantity() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>          price: \" + getPrice() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>       orderFee: \" + getOrderFee()\n   169→                + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>         symbol: \" + getSymbol() + \"</LI>\";\n   170→    }\n   171→\n   172→    public void print() {\n   173→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   174→    }\n   175→\n   176→    public Integer getOrderID() {\n   177→        return orderID;\n   178→    }\n   179→\n   180→    public void setOrderID(Integer orderID) {\n   181→        this.orderID = orderID;\n   182→    }\n   183→\n   184→    public String getOrderType() {\n   185→        return orderType;\n   186→    }\n   187→\n   188→    public void setOrderType(String orderType) {\n   189→        this.orderType = orderType;\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    public String getOrderStatus() {\n   193→        return orderStatus;\n   194→    }\n   195→\n   196→    public void setOrderStatus(String orderStatus) {\n   197→        this.orderStatus = orderStatus;\n   198→    }\n   199→\n   200→    public Date getOpenDate() {\n   201→        return openDate;\n   202→    }\n   203→\n   204→    public void setOpenDate(Date openDate) {\n   205→        this.openDate = openDate;\n   206→    }\n   207→\n   208→    public Date getCompletionDate() {\n   209→        return completionDate;\n   210→    }\n   211→\n   212→    public void setCompletionDate(Date completionDate) {\n   213→        this.completionDate = completionDate;\n   214→    }\n   215→\n   216→    public double getQuantity() {\n   217→        return quantity;\n   218→    }\n   219→\n   220→    public void setQuantity(double quantity) {\n   221→        this.quantity = quantity;\n   222→    }\n   223→\n   224→    public BigDecimal getPrice() {\n   225→        return price;\n   226→    }\n   227→\n   228→    public void setPrice(BigDecimal price) {\n   229→        this.price = price;\n   230→    }\n   231→\n   232→    public BigDecimal getOrderFee() {\n   233→        return orderFee;\n   234→    }\n   235→\n   236→    public void setOrderFee(BigDecimal orderFee) {\n   237→        this.orderFee = orderFee;\n   238→    }\n   239→\n   240→    public String getSymbol() {\n   241→        if (quote != null) {\n   242→            return quote.getSymbol();\n   243→        }\n   244→        return symbol;\n   245→    }\n   246→\n   247→    public void setSymbol(String symbol) {\n   248→        this.symbol = symbol;\n   249→    }\n   250→\n   251→    public AccountDataBean getAccount() {\n   252→        return account;\n   253→    }\n   254→\n   255→    public void setAccount(AccountDataBean account) {\n   256→        this.account = account;\n   257→    }\n   258→\n   259→    public QuoteDataBean getQuote() {\n   260→        return quote;\n   261→    }\n   262→\n   263→    public void setQuote(QuoteDataBean quote) {\n   264→        this.quote = quote;\n   265→    }\n   266→\n   267→    public HoldingDataBean getHolding() {\n   268→        return holding;\n   269→    }\n   270→\n   271→    public void setHolding(HoldingDataBean holding) {\n   272→        this.holding = holding;\n   273→    }\n   274→\n   275→    public boolean isBuy() {\n   276→        String orderType = getOrderType();\n   277→        if (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"buy\") == 0) {\n   278→            return true;\n   279→        }\n   280→        return false;\n   281→    }\n   282→\n   283→    public boolean isSell() {\n   284→        String orderType = getOrderType();\n   285→        if (orderType.compareToIgnoreCase(\"sell\") == 0) {\n   286→            return true;\n   287→        }\n   288→        return false;\n   289→    }\n   290→\n   291→    public boolean isOpen() {\n   292→        String orderStatus = getOrderStatus();\n   293→        if ((orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"open\") == 0) || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"processing\") == 0)) {\n   294→            return true;\n   295→        }\n   296→        return false;\n   297→    }\n   298→\n   299→    public boolean isCompleted() {\n   300→        String orderStatus = getOrderStatus();\n   301→        if ((orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"completed\") == 0) || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"alertcompleted\") == 0)\n   302→                || (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"cancelled\") == 0)) {\n   303→            return true;\n   304→        }\n   305→        return false;\n   306→    }\n   307→\n   308→    public boolean isCancelled() {\n   309→        String orderStatus = getOrderStatus();\n   310→        if (orderStatus.compareToIgnoreCase(\"cancelled\") == 0) {\n   311→            return true;\n   312→        }\n   313→        return false;\n   314→    }\n   315→\n   316→    public void cancel() {\n   317→        setOrderStatus(\"cancelled\");\n   318→    }\n   319→\n   320→    @Override\n   321→    public int hashCode() {\n   322→        int hash = 0;\n   323→        hash += (this.orderID != null ? this.orderID.hashCode() : 0);\n   324→        return hash;\n   325→    }\n   326→\n   327→    @Override\n   328→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   329→        \n   330→        if (!(object instanceof OrderDataBean)) {\n   331→            return false;\n   332→        }\n   333→        OrderDataBean other = (OrderDataBean) object;\n   334→        if (this.orderID != other.orderID && (this.orderID == null || !this.orderID.equals(other.orderID))) {\n   335→            return false;\n   336→        }\n   337→        return true;\n   338→    }\n   339→}\n   340→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"dc7f23cc-afeb-4c9d-9257-77f1bd9f94ef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DziStc5oidUJGs96osfmQV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.Date;\n    21→\n    22→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    23→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    24→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    25→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    26→import javax.persistence.GenerationType;\n    27→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    28→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    29→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    30→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    31→import javax.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    32→import javax.persistence.Temporal;\n    33→import javax.persistence.TemporalType;\n    34→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    35→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    36→import javax.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    37→import javax.validation.constraints.Positive;\n    38→\n    39→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    40→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    41→\n    42→@Entity(name = \"holdingejb\")\n    43→@Table(name = \"holdingejb\")\n    44→public class HoldingDataBean implements Serializable {\n    45→\n    46→    /* persistent/relationship fields */\n    47→\n    48→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -2338411656251935480L;\n    49→\n    50→    @Id\n    51→    @TableGenerator(name = \"holdingIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"holding\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    52→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"holdingIdGen\")\n    53→    @Column(name = \"HOLDINGID\", nullable = false)\n    54→    private Integer holdingID; /* holdingID */\n    55→\n    56→    @NotNull\n    57→    @Positive\n    58→    @Column(name = \"QUANTITY\", nullable = false)\n    59→    private double quantity; /* quantity */\n    60→\n    61→    @Column(name = \"PURCHASEPRICE\")\n    62→    @Positive\n    63→    private BigDecimal purchasePrice; /* purchasePrice */\n    64→\n    65→    @Column(name = \"PURCHASEDATE\")\n    66→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    67→    @PastOrPresent\n    68→    private Date purchaseDate; /* purchaseDate */\n    69→\n    70→    @Transient\n    71→    private String quoteID; /* Holding(*) ---> Quote(1) */\n    72→\n    73→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    74→    @JoinColumn(name = \"ACCOUNT_ACCOUNTID\")\n    75→    private AccountDataBean account;\n    76→\n    77→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n    78→    @JoinColumn(name = \"QUOTE_SYMBOL\")\n    79→    private QuoteDataBean quote;\n    80→\n    81→    public HoldingDataBean() {\n    82→    }\n    83→\n    84→    public HoldingDataBean(Integer holdingID, double quantity, BigDecimal purchasePrice, Date purchaseDate, String quoteID) {\n    85→        setHoldingID(holdingID);\n    86→        setQuantity(quantity);\n    87→        setPurchasePrice(purchasePrice);\n    88→        setPurchaseDate(purchaseDate);\n    89→        setQuoteID(quoteID);\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    public HoldingDataBean(double quantity, BigDecimal purchasePrice, Date purchaseDate, AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote) {\n    93→        setQuantity(quantity);\n    94→        setPurchasePrice(purchasePrice);\n    95→        setPurchaseDate(purchaseDate);\n    96→        setAccount(account);\n    97→        setQuote(quote);\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    public static HoldingDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   101→        return new HoldingDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), // holdingID\n   102→                TradeConfig.rndQuantity(), // quantity\n   103→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000.0f), // purchasePrice\n   104→                new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), // purchaseDate\n   105→                TradeConfig.rndSymbol() // symbol\n   106→        );\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    @Override\n   110→    public String toString() {\n   111→        return \"\\n\\tHolding Data for holding: \" + getHoldingID() + \"\\n\\t\\t      quantity:\" + getQuantity() + \"\\n\\t\\t purchasePrice:\" + getPurchasePrice()\n   112→                + \"\\n\\t\\t  purchaseDate:\" + getPurchaseDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t       quoteID:\" + getQuoteID();\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public String toHTML() {\n   116→        return \"<BR>Holding Data for holding: \" + getHoldingID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>      quantity:\" + getQuantity() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> purchasePrice:\"\n   117→                + getPurchasePrice() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  purchaseDate:\" + getPurchaseDate() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>       quoteID:\" + getQuoteID() + \"</LI>\";\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    public void print() {\n   121→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   122→    }\n   123→\n   124→    public Integer getHoldingID() {\n   125→        return holdingID;\n   126→    }\n   127→\n   128→    public void setHoldingID(Integer holdingID) {\n   129→        this.holdingID = holdingID;\n   130→    }\n   131→\n   132→    public double getQuantity() {\n   133→        return quantity;\n   134→    }\n   135→\n   136→    public void setQuantity(double quantity) {\n   137→        this.quantity = quantity;\n   138→    }\n   139→\n   140→    public BigDecimal getPurchasePrice() {\n   141→        return purchasePrice;\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    public void setPurchasePrice(BigDecimal purchasePrice) {\n   145→        this.purchasePrice = purchasePrice;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    public Date getPurchaseDate() {\n   149→        return purchaseDate;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public void setPurchaseDate(Date purchaseDate) {\n   153→        this.purchaseDate = purchaseDate;\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    public String getQuoteID() {\n   157→        if (quote != null) {\n   158→            return quote.getSymbol();\n   159→        }\n   160→        return quoteID;\n   161→    }\n   162→\n   163→    public void setQuoteID(String quoteID) {\n   164→        this.quoteID = quoteID;\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    public AccountDataBean getAccount() {\n   168→        return account;\n   169→    }\n   170→\n   171→    public void setAccount(AccountDataBean account) {\n   172→        this.account = account;\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    public QuoteDataBean getQuote() {\n   176→        return quote;\n   177→    }\n   178→\n   179→    public void setQuote(QuoteDataBean quote) {\n   180→        this.quote = quote;\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    @Override\n   184→    public int hashCode() {\n   185→        int hash = 0;\n   186→        hash += (this.holdingID != null ? this.holdingID.hashCode() : 0);\n   187→        return hash;\n   188→    }\n   189→\n   190→    @Override\n   191→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   192→        \n   193→        if (!(object instanceof HoldingDataBean)) {\n   194→            return false;\n   195→        }\n   196→        HoldingDataBean other = (HoldingDataBean) object;\n   197→\n   198→        if (this.holdingID != other.holdingID && (this.holdingID == null || !this.holdingID.equals(other.holdingID))) {\n   199→            return false;\n   200→        }\n   201→\n   202→        return true;\n   203→    }\n   204→}\n   205→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"df2d1b39-82e2-4dfd-ac50-6ecfd849a406"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0126cyNLPTNek5CZkaP1sB5n","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→//import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    19→\n    20→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    21→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n    22→import javax.persistence.FetchType;\n    23→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    24→import javax.persistence.OneToOne;\n    25→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    26→import javax.validation.constraints.Email;\n    27→import javax.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n    28→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    29→\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    32→\n    33→@Entity(name = \"accountprofileejb\")\n    34→@Table(name = \"accountprofileejb\")\n    35→public class AccountProfileDataBean implements java.io.Serializable {\n    36→\n    37→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    38→\n    39→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2794584136675420624L;\n    40→\n    41→    @Id\n    42→    @NotNull\n    43→    @Column(name = \"USERID\", nullable = false)\n    44→    private String userID; /* userID */\n    45→\n    46→    @Column(name = \"PASSWD\")\n    47→    @NotBlank\n    48→    private String passwd; /* password */\n    49→\n    50→    @Column(name = \"FULLNAME\")\n    51→    @NotBlank\n    52→    private String fullName; /* fullName */\n    53→\n    54→    @Column(name = \"ADDRESS\")\n    55→    @NotBlank\n    56→    private String address; /* address */\n    57→\n    58→    @Column(name = \"EMAIL\")\n    59→    @Email(message = \"Email should be valid\")\n    60→    private String email; /* email */\n    61→\n    62→    @Column(name = \"CREDITCARD\")\n    63→    @NotBlank\n    64→    private String creditCard; /* creditCard */\n    65→\n    66→    @OneToOne(mappedBy = \"profile\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    67→    private AccountDataBean account;\n    68→\n    69→    public AccountProfileDataBean() {\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    public AccountProfileDataBean(String userID, String password, String fullName, String address, String email, String creditCard) {\n    73→        setUserID(userID);\n    74→        setPassword(password);\n    75→        setFullName(fullName);\n    76→        setAddress(address);\n    77→        setEmail(email);\n    78→        setCreditCard(creditCard);\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    public static AccountProfileDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    82→        return new AccountProfileDataBean(TradeConfig.rndUserID(), // userID\n    83→                TradeConfig.rndUserID(), // passwd\n    84→                TradeConfig.rndFullName(), // fullname\n    85→                TradeConfig.rndAddress(), // address\n    86→                TradeConfig.rndEmail(TradeConfig.rndUserID()), // email\n    87→                TradeConfig.rndCreditCard() // creditCard\n    88→        );\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    @Override\n    92→    public String toString() {\n    93→        return \"\\n\\tAccount Profile Data for userID:\" + getUserID() + \"\\n\\t\\t   passwd:\" + getPassword() + \"\\n\\t\\t   fullName:\" + getFullName()\n    94→                + \"\\n\\t\\t    address:\" + getAddress() + \"\\n\\t\\t      email:\" + getEmail() + \"\\n\\t\\t creditCard:\" + getCreditCard();\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    public String toHTML() {\n    98→        return \"<BR>Account Profile Data for userID: <B>\" + getUserID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>   passwd:\" + getPassword() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>   fullName:\"\n    99→                + getFullName() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    address:\" + getAddress() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>      email:\" + getEmail() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> creditCard:\"\n   100→                + getCreditCard() + \"</LI>\";\n   101→    }\n   102→\n   103→    public void print() {\n   104→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    public String getUserID() {\n   108→        return userID;\n   109→    }\n   110→\n   111→    public void setUserID(String userID) {\n   112→        this.userID = userID;\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    public String getPassword() {\n   116→        return passwd;\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    public void setPassword(String password) {\n   120→        this.passwd = password;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    public String getFullName() {\n   124→        return fullName;\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public void setFullName(String fullName) {\n   128→        this.fullName = fullName;\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    public String getAddress() {\n   132→        return address;\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    public void setAddress(String address) {\n   136→        this.address = address;\n   137→    }\n   138→\n   139→    public String getEmail() {\n   140→        return email;\n   141→    }\n   142→\n   143→    public void setEmail(String email) {\n   144→        this.email = email;\n   145→    }\n   146→\n   147→    public String getCreditCard() {\n   148→        return creditCard;\n   149→    }\n   150→\n   151→    public void setCreditCard(String creditCard) {\n   152→        this.creditCard = creditCard;\n   153→    }\n   154→\n   155→    public AccountDataBean getAccount() {\n   156→        return account;\n   157→    }\n   158→\n   159→    public void setAccount(AccountDataBean account) {\n   160→        this.account = account;\n   161→    }\n   162→\n   163→    @Override\n   164→    public int hashCode() {\n   165→        int hash = 0;\n   166→        hash += (this.userID != null ? this.userID.hashCode() : 0);\n   167→        return hash;\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    @Override\n   171→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   172→       \n   173→        if (!(object instanceof AccountProfileDataBean)) {\n   174→            return false;\n   175→        }\n   176→        AccountProfileDataBean other = (AccountProfileDataBean) object;\n   177→\n   178→        if (this.userID != other.userID && (this.userID == null || !this.userID.equals(other.userID))) {\n   179→            return false;\n   180→        }\n   181→\n   182→        return true;\n   183→    }\n   184→}\n   185→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"db2d27d7-38b8-4d29-9141-1893b0c21acc"}
