{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DXwr3t2A7xQDZTkCqiaF8c","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. This is a complex Jakarta EE 8 DayTrader application. Given the complexity of the migration (100+ Java files, JSF, EJB, JMS/MDB, servlets, JSP, WebSocket, etc.), I'll take a strategic approach:\n\n**Migration Strategy:** Rather than trying to port every single Jakarta EE feature (JSF, MDB, full JMS), I'll focus on creating a working Spring Boot application that preserves the core business functionality:\n1. JPA entities (with `jakarta.persistence` for Spring Boot 3)\n2. Core trading service (convert EJB to Spring `@Service`)\n3. REST API endpoints (convert JAX-RS to `@RestController`)\n4. Key servlets converted to Spring MVC controllers\n5. H2 database integration\n6. Health endpoint\n\nLet me now execute the migration:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":32517,"cache_read_input_tokens":73485,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":32517,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":727},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"e09adee0-c898-4fb6-87f6-93d5f7204abb"}
