{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VhEXxQ8x37HjGVeKHZ4N48","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any;\n    22→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance;\n    23→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletConfig;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebServlet;\n    27→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServlet;\n    28→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n    29→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    30→\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    33→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    34→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;\n    35→\n    36→@WebServlet(name = \"TestServlet\", urlPatterns = { \"/TestServlet\" })\n    37→public class TestServlet extends HttpServlet {\n    38→\n    39→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -2927579146688173127L;\n    40→    \n    41→    private TradeServices tradeAction;\n    42→    \n    43→    @Inject \n    44→    public TestServlet(@Any Instance<TradeServices> services) {\n    45→      tradeAction = services.select(new TradeRunTimeModeLiteral(TradeConfig.getRunTimeModeNames()[TradeConfig.getRunTimeMode()])).get();\n    46→    }\n    47→    \n    48→    @Override\n    49→    public void init(ServletConfig config) throws ServletException {\n    50→        super.init(config);\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    /**\n    54→     * Process incoming HTTP GET requests\n    55→     *\n    56→     * @param request\n    57→     *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    58→     * @param response\n    59→     *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    60→     */\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    63→        performTask(request, response);\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * Process incoming HTTP POST requests\n    68→     *\n    69→     * @param request\n    70→     *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    71→     * @param response\n    72→     *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    73→     */\n    74→    @Override\n    75→    public void doPost(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    76→        performTask(request, response);\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    /**\n    80→     * Main service method for TradeAppServlet\n    81→     *\n    82→     * @param request\n    83→     *            Object that encapsulates the request to the servlet\n    84→     * @param response\n    85→     *            Object that encapsulates the response from the servlet\n    86→     */\n    87→    public void performTask(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    88→        try {\n    89→            Log.debug(\"Enter TestServlet doGet\");\n    90→            //TradeDirect tradeDirect = new TradeDirect();\n    91→            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {\n    92→                tradeAction.createQuote(\"s:\" + i, \"Company \" + i, new BigDecimal(i * 1.1));\n    93→            }\n    94→            /*\n    95→             *\n    96→             * AccountDataBean accountData = new TradeAction().register(\"user1\",\n    97→             * \"password\", \"fullname\", \"address\", \"email\", \"creditCard\", new\n    98→             * BigDecimal(123.45), false);\n    99→             *\n   100→             * OrderDataBean orderData = new TradeAction().buy(\"user1\", \"s:1\",\n   101→             * 100.0); orderData = new TradeAction().buy(\"user1\", \"s:2\", 200.0);\n   102→             * Thread.sleep(5000); accountData = new\n   103→             * TradeAction().getAccountData(\"user1\"); Collection\n   104→             * holdingDataBeans = new TradeAction().getHoldings(\"user1\");\n   105→             * PrintWriter out = resp.getWriter();\n   106→             * resp.setContentType(\"text/html\");\n   107→             * out.write(\"<HEAD></HEAD><BODY><BR><BR>\");\n   108→             * out.write(accountData.toString());\n   109→             * Log.printCollection(\"user1 Holdings\", holdingDataBeans);\n   110→             * ServletContext sc = getServletContext();\n   111→             * req.setAttribute(\"results\", \"Success\");\n   112→             * req.setAttribute(\"accountData\", accountData);\n   113→             * req.setAttribute(\"holdingDataBeans\", holdingDataBeans);\n   114→             * getServletContext\n   115→             * ().getRequestDispatcher(\"/tradehome.jsp\").include(req, resp);\n   116→             * out.write(\"<BR><BR>done.</BODY>\");\n   117→             */\n   118→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   119→            Log.error(\"TestServletException\", e);\n   120→        }\n   121→    }\n   122→}\n   123→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"ec6afe0e-9839-435c-8482-2c9daa1ac3a9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015CtVrcdMdCvR2GhdCGuMbE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015, 2022.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.web.servlet;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.IOException;\n    19→\n    20→import jakarta.servlet.Filter;\n    21→import jakarta.servlet.FilterChain;\n    22→import jakarta.servlet.FilterConfig;\n    23→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n    24→import jakarta.servlet.ServletRequest;\n    25→import jakarta.servlet.ServletResponse;\n    26→import jakarta.servlet.annotation.WebFilter;\n    27→\n    28→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Diagnostics;\n    30→\n    31→@WebFilter(filterName = \"PrimFilter\", urlPatterns = \"/drive/*\")\n    32→@Trace\n    33→public class PrimFilter implements Filter {\n    34→\t\n    35→  /**\n    36→   * @see Filter#init(FilterConfig)\n    37→   */\n    38→  private FilterConfig filterConfig = null;\n    39→\n    40→  @Override\n    41→  public void init(FilterConfig filterConfig) throws ServletException {\n    42→    this.filterConfig = filterConfig;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  /**\n    46→   * @see Filter#doFilter(ServletRequest, ServletResponse, FilterChain)\n    47→   */\n    48→  @Override\n    49→  public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse resp, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {\n    50→\n    51→    if (filterConfig == null) {\n    52→      return;\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    Diagnostics.checkDiagnostics();\n    56→\n    57→    chain.doFilter(req, resp/* wrapper */);\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  /**\n    61→   * @see Filter#destroy()\n    62→   */\n    63→  @Override\n    64→  public void destroy() {\n    65→    this.filterConfig = null;\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"1d5871cb-d9b8-4307-b868-9097084c83de"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RAwbp4beKEf79wqXmtKWeG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces;\n    17→\n    18→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.concurrent.Future;\n    21→\n    22→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans.MarketSummaryDataBean;\n    23→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountDataBean;\n    24→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.AccountProfileDataBean;\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.HoldingDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.OrderDataBean;\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→\n    29→/**\n    30→ * TradeServices interface specifies the business methods provided by the Trade\n    31→ * online broker application. These business methods represent the features and\n    32→ * operations that can be performed by customers of the brokerage such as login,\n    33→ * logout, get a stock quote, buy or sell a stock, etc. This interface is\n    34→ * implemented by {@link Trade} providing an EJB implementation of these\n    35→ * business methods and also by {@link TradeDirect} providing a JDBC\n    36→ * implementation.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * @see TradeDirect\n    39→ * @see TradeSLSB\n    40→ *\n    41→ */\n    42→\n    43→public interface TradeServices {\n    44→\n    45→    /**\n    46→     * Compute and return a snapshot of the current market conditions This\n    47→     * includes the TSIA - an index of the price of the top 100 Trade stock\n    48→     * quotes The openTSIA ( the index at the open) The volume of shares traded,\n    49→     * Top Stocks gain and loss\n    50→     *\n    51→     * @return A snapshot of the current market summary\n    52→     */\n    53→    MarketSummaryDataBean getMarketSummary() throws Exception;\n    54→\n    55→    /**\n    56→     * Create an order (buy or sell)\n    57→     *\n    58→     * @param accoount\n    59→     *            the accountdatabean\n    60→     * @param quote\n    61→     *            the quptedatabean\n    62→     * @param holding\n    63→     *            the holdingdatabean\n    64→     * @param orderType\n    65→     *            buy or sell\n    66→     * @param quantity\n    67→     *            quantity            \n    68→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n    69→     */\n    70→    OrderDataBean createOrder(AccountDataBean account, QuoteDataBean quote, HoldingDataBean holding, String orderType,\n    71→        double quantity) throws Exception;\n    72→    \n    73→    /**\n    74→     * Purchase a stock and create a new holding for the given user. Given a\n    75→     * stock symbol and quantity to purchase, retrieve the current quote price,\n    76→     * debit the user's account balance, and add holdings to user's portfolio.\n    77→     * buy/sell are asynchronous, using J2EE messaging, A new order is created\n    78→     * and submitted for processing to the TradeBroker\n    79→     *\n    80→     * @param userID\n    81→     *            the customer requesting the stock purchase\n    82→     * @param symbol\n    83→     *            the symbol of the stock being purchased\n    84→     * @param quantity\n    85→     *            the quantity of shares to purchase\n    86→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created buy order\n    87→     */\n    88→\n    89→    OrderDataBean buy(String userID, String symbol, double quantity, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n    90→\n    91→    /**\n    92→     * Sell a stock holding and removed the holding for the given user. Given a\n    93→     * Holding, retrieve current quote, credit user's account, and reduce\n    94→     * holdings in user's portfolio.\n    95→     *\n    96→     * @param userID\n    97→     *            the customer requesting the sell\n    98→     * @param holdingID\n    99→     *            the users holding to be sold\n   100→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the newly created sell\n   101→     *         order\n   102→     */\n   103→    OrderDataBean sell(String userID, Integer holdingID, int orderProcessingMode) throws Exception;\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Queue the Order identified by orderID to be processed\n   107→     *\n   108→     * Orders are submitted through JMS to a Trading Broker and completed\n   109→     * asynchronously. This method queues the order for processing\n   110→     *\n   111→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   112→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   113→     *\n   114→     * @param orderID\n   115→     *            the Order being queued for processing\n   116→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   117→     */\n   118→    void queueOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   119→\n   120→    /**\n   121→     * Complete the Order identified by orderID. This method completes\n   122→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   123→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   124→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   125→     *\n   126→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   127→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   128→     *\n   129→     * @param orderID\n   130→     *            the Order to complete\n   131→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   132→     */\n   133→    OrderDataBean completeOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   134→\n   135→    /**\n   136→     * Complete the Order identefied by orderID Orders are completed \n   137→     * asynchronously. This method completes\n   138→     * the order For a buy, the stock is purchased creating a holding and the\n   139→     * users account is debited For a sell, the stock holding is removed and the\n   140→     * users account is credited with the proceeds\n   141→     *\n   142→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   143→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   144→     *\n   145→     * @param orderID\n   146→     *            the Order to complete\n   147→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   148→     */\n   149→    Future<OrderDataBean> completeOrderAsync(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   150→    \n   151→    /**\n   152→     * Cancel the Order identefied by orderID\n   153→     *\n   154→     * The boolean twoPhase specifies to the server implementation whether or\n   155→     * not the method is to participate in a global transaction\n   156→     *\n   157→     * @param orderID\n   158→     *            the Order to complete\n   159→     * @return OrderDataBean providing the status of the completed order\n   160→     */\n   161→    void cancelOrder(Integer orderID, boolean twoPhase) throws Exception;\n   162→\n   163→    /**\n   164→     * Signify an order has been completed for the given userID\n   165→     *\n   166→     * @param userID\n   167→     *            the user for which an order has completed\n   168→     * @param orderID\n   169→     *            the order which has completed\n   170→     *\n   171→     */\n   172→    void orderCompleted(String userID, Integer orderID) throws Exception;\n   173→\n   174→    /**\n   175→     * Get the collection of all orders for a given account\n   176→     *\n   177→     * @param userID\n   178→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   179→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   180→     */\n   181→    Collection<?> getOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   182→\n   183→    /**\n   184→     * Get the collection of completed orders for a given account that need to\n   185→     * be alerted to the user\n   186→     *\n   187→     * @param userID\n   188→     *            the customer account to retrieve orders for\n   189→     * @return Collection OrderDataBeans providing detailed order information\n   190→     */\n   191→    Collection<?> getClosedOrders(String userID) throws Exception;\n   192→\n   193→    /**\n   194→     * Given a market symbol, price, and details, create and return a new\n   195→     * {@link QuoteDataBean}\n   196→     *\n   197→     * @param symbol\n   198→     *            the symbol of the stock\n   199→     * @param price\n   200→     *            the current stock price\n   201→     * @param details\n   202→     *            a short description of the stock or company\n   203→     * @return a new QuoteDataBean or null if Quote could not be created\n   204→     */\n   205→    QuoteDataBean createQuote(String symbol, String companyName, BigDecimal price) throws Exception;\n   206→\n   207→    /**\n   208→     * Return a {@link QuoteDataBean} describing a current quote for the given\n   209→     * stock symbol\n   210→     *\n   211→     * @param symbol\n   212→     *            the stock symbol to retrieve the current Quote\n   213→     * @return the QuoteDataBean\n   214→     */\n   215→    QuoteDataBean getQuote(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   216→\n   217→    /**\n   218→     * Return a {@link java.util.Collection} of {@link QuoteDataBean} describing\n   219→     * all current quotes\n   220→     *\n   221→     * @return A collection of QuoteDataBean\n   222→     */\n   223→    Collection<?> getAllQuotes() throws Exception;\n   224→\n   225→    /**\n   226→     * Update the stock quote price and volume for the specified stock symbol\n   227→     *\n   228→     * @param symbol\n   229→     *            for stock quote to update\n   230→     * @param price\n   231→     *            the updated quote price\n   232→     * @return the QuoteDataBean describing the stock\n   233→     */\n   234→    QuoteDataBean updateQuotePriceVolume(String symbol, BigDecimal newPrice, double sharesTraded) throws Exception;\n   235→\n   236→    /**\n   237→     * Return the portfolio of stock holdings for the specified customer as a\n   238→     * collection of HoldingDataBeans\n   239→     *\n   240→     * @param userID\n   241→     *            the customer requesting the portfolio\n   242→     * @return Collection of the users portfolio of stock holdings\n   243→     */\n   244→    Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings(String userID) throws Exception;\n   245→\n   246→    /**\n   247→     * Return a specific user stock holding identifed by the holdingID\n   248→     *\n   249→     * @param holdingID\n   250→     *            the holdingID to return\n   251→     * @return a HoldingDataBean describing the holding\n   252→     */\n   253→    HoldingDataBean getHolding(Integer holdingID) throws Exception;\n   254→\n   255→    /**\n   256→     * Return an AccountDataBean object for userID describing the account\n   257→     *\n   258→     * @param userID\n   259→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   260→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   261→     */\n   262→    AccountDataBean getAccountData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   263→\n   264→    /**\n   265→     * Return an AccountProfileDataBean for userID providing the users profile\n   266→     *\n   267→     * @param userID\n   268→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   269→     * @param User\n   270→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   271→     */\n   272→    AccountProfileDataBean getAccountProfileData(String userID) throws Exception;\n   273→\n   274→    /**\n   275→     * Update userID's account profile information using the provided\n   276→     * AccountProfileDataBean object\n   277→     *\n   278→     * @param userID\n   279→     *            the account userID to lookup\n   280→     * @param User\n   281→     *            account profile data in AccountProfileDataBean\n   282→     */\n   283→    AccountProfileDataBean updateAccountProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profileData) throws Exception;\n   284→\n   285→    /**\n   286→     * Attempt to authenticate and login a user with the given password\n   287→     *\n   288→     * @param userID\n   289→     *            the customer to login\n   290→     * @param password\n   291→     *            the password entered by the customer for authentication\n   292→     * @return User account data in AccountDataBean\n   293→     */\n   294→    AccountDataBean login(String userID, String password) throws Exception;\n   295→\n   296→    /**\n   297→     * Logout the given user\n   298→     *\n   299→     * @param userID\n   300→     *            the customer to logout\n   301→     * @return the login status\n   302→     */\n   303→\n   304→    void logout(String userID) throws Exception;\n   305→\n   306→    /**\n   307→     * Register a new Trade customer. Create a new user profile, user registry\n   308→     * entry, account with initial balance, and empty portfolio.\n   309→     *\n   310→     * @param userID\n   311→     *            the new customer to register\n   312→     * @param password\n   313→     *            the customers password\n   314→     * @param fullname\n   315→     *            the customers fullname\n   316→     * @param address\n   317→     *            the customers street address\n   318→     * @param email\n   319→     *            the customers email address\n   320→     * @param creditcard\n   321→     *            the customers creditcard number\n   322→     * @param initialBalance\n   323→     *            the amount to charge to the customers credit to open the\n   324→     *            account and set the initial balance\n   325→     * @return the userID if successful, null otherwise\n   326→     */\n   327→    AccountDataBean register(String userID, String password, String fullname, String address, String email, String creditcard, BigDecimal openBalance)\n   328→            throws Exception;\n   329→\n   330→    \n   331→    int getImpl();\n   332→\n   333→    QuoteDataBean pingTwoPhase(String symbol) throws Exception;\n   334→\n   335→    double investmentReturn(double rnd1, double rnd2) throws Exception;\n   336→\n   337→    void setInSession(boolean inSession);\n   338→}\n   339→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"58c884ec-79a3-4c6c-a989-b606e9afceec"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Apn8hHcJcEtGghwfyJCszA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.jaxrs;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    19→import java.util.List;\n    20→\n    21→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    22→import org.springframework.http.MediaType;\n    23→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n    24→\n    25→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    26→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.TradeServices;\n    27→\n    28→@RestController\n    29→@RequestMapping(\"/rest/quotes\")\n    30→public class QuoteResource {\n    31→\n    32→    @Autowired\n    33→    private TradeServices tradeService;\n    34→\n    35→    @GetMapping(value = \"/{symbols}\", produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    36→    public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesGet(@PathVariable(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    37→        return getQuotes(symbols);\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @PostMapping(consumes = MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED_VALUE, produces = MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)\n    41→    public List<QuoteDataBean> quotesPost(@RequestParam(\"symbols\") String symbols) {\n    42→        return getQuotes(symbols);\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    private List<QuoteDataBean> getQuotes(String symbols) {\n    46→        ArrayList<QuoteDataBean> quoteDataBeans = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    47→\n    48→        try {\n    49→            String[] symbolsSplit = symbols.split(\",\");\n    50→            for (String symbol : symbolsSplit) {\n    51→                QuoteDataBean quoteData = tradeService.getQuote(symbol);\n    52→                quoteDataBeans.add(quoteData);\n    53→            }\n    54→        } catch (Exception e) {\n    55→            e.printStackTrace();\n    56→        }\n    57→\n    58→        return (List<QuoteDataBean>) quoteDataBeans;\n    59→    }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"bb698be6-ed15-455a-b9ca-47e1547f9792"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L67v2X961D8ABNZ11ydLw8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2019.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→import java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\n    20→\n    21→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    22→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    23→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Size;\n    24→\n    25→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    26→\n    27→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    28→\n    29→/** This class holds the last 5 stock changes, used by the MarketSummary\n    30→ *  CDI event firing has been removed in Spring Boot migration\n    31→ **/\n    32→\n    33→@Component\n    34→public class RecentQuotePriceChangeList {\n    35→\n    36→    private List<QuoteDataBean> list = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    37→    private int maxSize = 5;\n    38→\n    39→    public boolean add(QuoteDataBean quoteData) {\n    40→        int symbolNumber = new Integer(quoteData.getSymbol().substring(2));\n    41→\n    42→        if (symbolNumber < TradeConfig.getMAX_QUOTES() * TradeConfig.getListQuotePriceChangeFrequency() * 0.01) {\n    43→            list.add(0, quoteData);\n    44→\n    45→            // Add stock, remove if needed\n    46→            if (list.size() > maxSize) {\n    47→                list.remove(maxSize);\n    48→            }\n    49→        }\n    50→        return true;\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public boolean isEmpty() {\n    54→        return list.isEmpty();\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    @Size(max = 5)\n    58→    @NotEmpty\n    59→    public List<@NotNull QuoteDataBean> recentList() {\n    60→        return list;\n    61→    }\n    62→}\n    63→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"b7c7db0f-fb7b-45b3-928d-59e0f71d6e51"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T5C1VnXttUXYpjyGBm77Nh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.beans;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.Date;\n    23→import java.util.Iterator;\n    24→\n    25→import jakarta.json.Json;\n    26→import jakarta.json.JsonObject;\n    27→import jakarta.json.JsonObjectBuilder;\n    28→\n    29→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities.QuoteDataBean;\n    30→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.FinancialUtils;\n    31→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    32→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    33→\n    34→public class MarketSummaryDataBean implements Serializable {\n    35→\n    36→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 650652242288745600L;\n    37→    private BigDecimal TSIA; /* Trade Stock Index Average */\n    38→    private BigDecimal openTSIA; /* Trade Stock Index Average at the open */\n    39→    private double volume; /* volume of shares traded */\n    40→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers; /*\n    41→                                                   * Collection of top gaining\n    42→                                                   * stocks\n    43→                                                   */\n    44→    private Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers; /*\n    45→                                                  * Collection of top losing\n    46→                                                  * stocks\n    47→                                                  */\n    48→    // FUTURE private Collection topVolume; /* Collection of top stocks by\n    49→    // volume */\n    50→    private Date summaryDate; /* Date this summary was taken */\n    51→\n    52→    // cache the gainPercent once computed for this bean\n    53→    private BigDecimal gainPercent = null;\n    54→\n    55→    public MarketSummaryDataBean() {\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public MarketSummaryDataBean(BigDecimal TSIA, BigDecimal openTSIA, double volume, Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers, Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers// , Collection topVolume\n    59→    ) {\n    60→        setTSIA(TSIA);\n    61→        setOpenTSIA(openTSIA);\n    62→        setVolume(volume);\n    63→        setTopGainers(topGainers);\n    64→        setTopLosers(topLosers);\n    65→        setSummaryDate(new java.sql.Date(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n    66→        gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n    67→\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    public static MarketSummaryDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n    71→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> gain = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    72→        Collection<QuoteDataBean> lose = new ArrayList<QuoteDataBean>();\n    73→\n    74→        for (int ii = 0; ii < 5; ii++) {\n    75→            QuoteDataBean quote1 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    76→            QuoteDataBean quote2 = QuoteDataBean.getRandomInstance();\n    77→\n    78→            gain.add(quote1);\n    79→            lose.add(quote2);\n    80→        }\n    81→\n    82→        return new MarketSummaryDataBean(TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), TradeConfig.rndQuantity(), gain, lose);\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    @Override\n    86→    public String toString() {\n    87→        String ret = \"\\n\\tMarket Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t        TSIA:\" + getTSIA() + \"\\n\\t\\t    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA()\n    88→                + \"\\n\\t\\t        gain:\" + getGainPercent() + \"\\n\\t\\t      volume:\" + getVolume();\n    89→\n    90→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n    91→            return ret;\n    92→        }\n    93→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Gainers:\";\n    94→        Iterator<QuoteDataBean> it = getTopGainers().iterator();\n    95→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n    96→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n    97→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n    98→        }\n    99→        ret += \"\\n\\t\\t   Current Top Losers:\";\n   100→        it = getTopLosers().iterator();\n   101→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   102→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   103→            ret += (\"\\n\\t\\t\\t\" + quoteData.toString());\n   104→        }\n   105→        return ret;\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    public String toHTML() {\n   109→        String ret = \"<BR>Market Summary at: \" + getSummaryDate() + \"<LI>        TSIA:\" + getTSIA() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    openTSIA:\" + getOpenTSIA() + \"</LI>\"\n   110→                + \"<LI>      volume:\" + getVolume() + \"</LI>\";\n   111→        if ((getTopGainers() == null) || (getTopLosers() == null)) {\n   112→            return ret;\n   113→        }\n   114→        ret += \"<BR> Current Top Gainers:\";\n   115→        Iterator<QuoteDataBean> it = getTopGainers().iterator();\n   116→\n   117→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   118→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   119→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   120→        }\n   121→        ret += \"<BR>   Current Top Losers:\";\n   122→        it = getTopLosers().iterator();\n   123→        while (it.hasNext()) {\n   124→            QuoteDataBean quoteData = it.next();\n   125→            ret += (\"<LI>\" + quoteData.toString() + \"</LI>\");\n   126→        }\n   127→        return ret;\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    public JsonObject toJSON() {\n   131→        \n   132→        JsonObjectBuilder jObjectBuilder = Json.createObjectBuilder();\n   133→        \n   134→        int i = 1;\n   135→        for (Iterator<QuoteDataBean> iterator = topGainers.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n   136→            QuoteDataBean quote = iterator.next();\n   137→\n   138→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"gainer\" + i + \"_stock\",quote.getSymbol());\n   139→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"gainer\" + i + \"_price\",\"$\" + quote.getPrice());\n   140→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"gainer\" + i + \"_change\",quote.getChange());\n   141→            i++;\n   142→        }\n   143→\n   144→        i = 1;\n   145→        for (Iterator<QuoteDataBean> iterator = topLosers.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n   146→            QuoteDataBean quote = iterator.next();\n   147→\n   148→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"loser\" + i + \"_stock\",quote.getSymbol());\n   149→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"loser\" + i + \"_price\",\"$\" + quote.getPrice());\n   150→            jObjectBuilder.add(\"loser\" + i + \"_change\",quote.getChange());\n   151→            i++;\n   152→        }\n   153→\n   154→        jObjectBuilder.add(\"tsia\", TSIA);\n   155→        jObjectBuilder.add(\"volume\",volume);\n   156→        jObjectBuilder.add(\"date\", summaryDate.toString());\n   157→\n   158→        return jObjectBuilder.build();\n   159→        \n   160→    }\n   161→\n   162→    public void print() {\n   163→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    public BigDecimal getGainPercent() {\n   167→        if (gainPercent == null) {\n   168→            gainPercent = FinancialUtils.computeGainPercent(getTSIA(), getOpenTSIA());\n   169→        }\n   170→        return gainPercent;\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    /**\n   174→     * Gets the tSIA\n   175→     *\n   176→     * @return Returns a BigDecimal\n   177→     */\n   178→    public BigDecimal getTSIA() {\n   179→        return TSIA;\n   180→    }\n   181→\n   182→    /**\n   183→     * Sets the tSIA\n   184→     *\n   185→     * @param tSIA\n   186→     *            The tSIA to set\n   187→     */\n   188→    public void setTSIA(BigDecimal tSIA) {\n   189→        TSIA = tSIA;\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    /**\n   193→     * Gets the openTSIA\n   194→     *\n   195→     * @return Returns a BigDecimal\n   196→     */\n   197→    public BigDecimal getOpenTSIA() {\n   198→        return openTSIA;\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    /**\n   202→     * Sets the openTSIA\n   203→     *\n   204→     * @param openTSIA\n   205→     *            The openTSIA to set\n   206→     */\n   207→    public void setOpenTSIA(BigDecimal openTSIA) {\n   208→        this.openTSIA = openTSIA;\n   209→    }\n   210→\n   211→    /**\n   212→     * Gets the volume\n   213→     *\n   214→     * @return Returns a BigDecimal\n   215→     */\n   216→    public double getVolume() {\n   217→        return volume;\n   218→    }\n   219→\n   220→    /**\n   221→     * Sets the volume\n   222→     *\n   223→     * @param volume\n   224→     *            The volume to set\n   225→     */\n   226→    public void setVolume(double volume) {\n   227→        this.volume = volume;\n   228→    }\n   229→\n   230→    /**\n   231→     * Gets the topGainers\n   232→     *\n   233→     * @return Returns a Collection\n   234→     */\n   235→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopGainers() {\n   236→        return topGainers;\n   237→    }\n   238→\n   239→    /**\n   240→     * Sets the topGainers\n   241→     *\n   242→     * @param topGainers\n   243→     *            The topGainers to set\n   244→     */\n   245→    public void setTopGainers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topGainers) {\n   246→        this.topGainers = topGainers;\n   247→    }\n   248→\n   249→    /**\n   250→     * Gets the topLosers\n   251→     *\n   252→     * @return Returns a Collection\n   253→     */\n   254→    public Collection<QuoteDataBean> getTopLosers() {\n   255→        return topLosers;\n   256→    }\n   257→\n   258→    /**\n   259→     * Sets the topLosers\n   260→     *\n   261→     * @param topLosers\n   262→     *            The topLosers to set\n   263→     */\n   264→    public void setTopLosers(Collection<QuoteDataBean> topLosers) {\n   265→        this.topLosers = topLosers;\n   266→    }\n   267→\n   268→    /**\n   269→     * Gets the summaryDate\n   270→     *\n   271→     * @return Returns a Date\n   272→     */\n   273→    public Date getSummaryDate() {\n   274→        return summaryDate;\n   275→    }\n   276→\n   277→    /**\n   278→     * Sets the summaryDate\n   279→     *\n   280→     * @param summaryDate\n   281→     *            The summaryDate to set\n   282→     */\n   283→    public void setSummaryDate(Date summaryDate) {\n   284→        this.summaryDate = summaryDate;\n   285→    }\n   286→\n   287→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"daf58cf5-636b-4709-b366-4ca6c8e2279e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Dvo33XjWFXmnhgjtRdCFzu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive view of remaining issues. Let me fix all the problematic files. The issues are:\n\n1. **TradeAppServlet.java** - Has `javax.servlet.http.*` in method signatures, `PushBuilder` (removed in Servlet 6.0), `@Trace` and `@Inject` from deleted interfaces\n2. **TradeServletAction.java** - Has `javax.servlet.ServletException` in method signatures, `javax.ejb.FinderException` \n3. **TradeScenarioServlet.java** - Has `javax.servlet.http.*` in method signatures\n4. **TradeWebContextListener.java** - Has `javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig` import\n5. **TradeConfigServlet.java** - References `TradeDirectDBUtils` (deleted) and `@Trace`\n6. **OrdersAlertFilter.java** - Uses CDI `Instance`, `@Trace`, `TradeRunTimeModeLiteral`\n7. **TestServlet.java** - Uses CDI `Instance`, `TradeRunTimeModeLiteral`\n8. **PrimFilter.java** - References `@Trace`\n\nLet me fix all of these files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29020,"cache_read_input_tokens":103073,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":29020,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1651},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"b3293f6b-d0e6-45af-a7b9-7630b527681b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Dvo33XjWFXmnhgjtRdCFzu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_012cytam7rdytdbG3QvQJjiy","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Fix all remaining Java files with javax/CDI issues","prompt":"Fix all the remaining Java files that have issues in the DayTrader Spring Boot migration at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nRead each file first, then Write the corrected version. Here are the exact fixes needed:\n\n### 1. TradeAppServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Line 29: `import jakarta.servlet.http.PushBuilder;` - PushBuilder removed in Servlet 6.0\n- Line 31: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - Trace was deleted\n- Line 45: `@Trace` - delete this annotation  \n- Line 48: `@Inject` should be changed to `@Autowired` from Spring\n- Line 92: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest` -> `HttpServletRequest`\n- Line 105: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse` -> `HttpServletResponse`\n- Lines 165-218: Remove the pushHeaderImages method and its call on line 166\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 2. TradeServletAction.java\nProblems:\n- Line 88, 149, 250, 319: `javax.servlet.ServletException` -> `ServletException` (already imported as jakarta)\n- Line 278: `javax.ejb.FinderException` - replace with generic Exception\n- Javadoc comments contain `@exception javax.servlet.ServletException` - change to `@exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException`\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 3. TradeScenarioServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Line 82: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest` -> `HttpServletRequest` \n- Line 95: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse` -> `HttpServletResponse`\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 4. TradeWebContextListener.java\nProblems:\n- Line 18: `import static javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig.Version.JSF_2_3;` - DELETE this line entirely (JSF removed)\n- Any `@FacesConfig` annotation - DELETE\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 5. TradeConfigServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Line 30: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirectDBUtils;` - This class was deleted\n- Line 31: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - This was deleted\n- Line 43: `@Trace` - remove annotation\n- Line 46-47: `@Inject private TradeDirectDBUtils dbUtils;` - We need to either keep TradeDirectDBUtils or remove usages\n\nSOLUTION for TradeConfigServlet: Remove all dbUtils usage. Remove the resetTrade and buildDB actions. Keep only the config display/update functionality. Replace `@Inject` with `@Autowired` and remove Trace import.\n\n### 6. OrdersAlertFilter.java\nProblems:\n- Lines 21-22: `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any`, `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance` - CDI not in Spring\n- Line 33: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - deleted\n- Line 38: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;` - deleted\n- Line 41: `@Trace` - remove\n- Lines 46-50: CDI Instance constructor - replace with simple @Autowired\n\nWrite the complete fixed file using `@Autowired private TradeServices tradeAction;` field injection and a default constructor.\n\n### 7. TestServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Lines 21-23: `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any`, `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance`, `jakarta.inject.Inject` \n- Line 34: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;` - deleted\n- Lines 43-46: CDI Instance constructor\n\nFix by using `@Autowired private TradeServices tradeAction;` field injection.\n\n### 8. PrimFilter.java  \nProblem:\n- Line 28: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - deleted\n- Line 32: `@Trace` - remove\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 9. Diagnostics.java - Check if it uses any javax imports\n### 10. MDBStats.java - Check if it uses any javax imports  \n### 11. KeyBlock.java - Check if it uses any javax imports\n### 12. TimerStat.java - Check if it uses any javax imports\n\nAlso check the entity files (AccountDataBean.java, AccountProfileDataBean.java, HoldingDataBean.java, OrderDataBean.java, QuoteDataBean.java) and make sure they use `jakarta.persistence.*` not `javax.persistence.*`.\n\nAlso check RunStatsDataBean.java and beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java for any javax references.\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file BEFORE writing it. Write the COMPLETE corrected content for each file.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29020,"cache_read_input_tokens":103073,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":29020,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1651},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"5a1b90ac-440f-4ec1-997d-ff5ff4a1214a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fix all the remaining Java files that have issues in the DayTrader Spring Boot migration at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__daytrader__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nRead each file first, then Write the corrected version. Here are the exact fixes needed:\n\n### 1. TradeAppServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Line 29: `import jakarta.servlet.http.PushBuilder;` - PushBuilder removed in Servlet 6.0\n- Line 31: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - Trace was deleted\n- Line 45: `@Trace` - delete this annotation  \n- Line 48: `@Inject` should be changed to `@Autowired` from Spring\n- Line 92: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest` -> `HttpServletRequest`\n- Line 105: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse` -> `HttpServletResponse`\n- Lines 165-218: Remove the pushHeaderImages method and its call on line 166\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 2. TradeServletAction.java\nProblems:\n- Line 88, 149, 250, 319: `javax.servlet.ServletException` -> `ServletException` (already imported as jakarta)\n- Line 278: `javax.ejb.FinderException` - replace with generic Exception\n- Javadoc comments contain `@exception javax.servlet.ServletException` - change to `@exception jakarta.servlet.ServletException`\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 3. TradeScenarioServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Line 82: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest` -> `HttpServletRequest` \n- Line 95: `javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse` -> `HttpServletResponse`\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 4. TradeWebContextListener.java\nProblems:\n- Line 18: `import static javax.faces.annotation.FacesConfig.Version.JSF_2_3;` - DELETE this line entirely (JSF removed)\n- Any `@FacesConfig` annotation - DELETE\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 5. TradeConfigServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Line 30: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.impl.direct.TradeDirectDBUtils;` - This class was deleted\n- Line 31: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - This was deleted\n- Line 43: `@Trace` - remove annotation\n- Line 46-47: `@Inject private TradeDirectDBUtils dbUtils;` - We need to either keep TradeDirectDBUtils or remove usages\n\nSOLUTION for TradeConfigServlet: Remove all dbUtils usage. Remove the resetTrade and buildDB actions. Keep only the config display/update functionality. Replace `@Inject` with `@Autowired` and remove Trace import.\n\n### 6. OrdersAlertFilter.java\nProblems:\n- Lines 21-22: `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any`, `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance` - CDI not in Spring\n- Line 33: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - deleted\n- Line 38: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;` - deleted\n- Line 41: `@Trace` - remove\n- Lines 46-50: CDI Instance constructor - replace with simple @Autowired\n\nWrite the complete fixed file using `@Autowired private TradeServices tradeAction;` field injection and a default constructor.\n\n### 7. TestServlet.java\nProblems:\n- Lines 21-23: `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Any`, `jakarta.enterprise.inject.Instance`, `jakarta.inject.Inject` \n- Line 34: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeRunTimeModeLiteral;` - deleted\n- Lines 43-46: CDI Instance constructor\n\nFix by using `@Autowired private TradeServices tradeAction;` field injection.\n\n### 8. PrimFilter.java  \nProblem:\n- Line 28: `import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.interfaces.Trace;` - deleted\n- Line 32: `@Trace` - remove\n\nWrite the complete fixed file.\n\n### 9. Diagnostics.java - Check if it uses any javax imports\n### 10. MDBStats.java - Check if it uses any javax imports  \n### 11. KeyBlock.java - Check if it uses any javax imports\n### 12. TimerStat.java - Check if it uses any javax imports\n\nAlso check the entity files (AccountDataBean.java, AccountProfileDataBean.java, HoldingDataBean.java, OrderDataBean.java, QuoteDataBean.java) and make sure they use `jakarta.persistence.*` not `javax.persistence.*`.\n\nAlso check RunStatsDataBean.java and beans/MarketSummaryDataBean.java for any javax references.\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file BEFORE writing it. Write the COMPLETE corrected content for each file."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012cytam7rdytdbG3QvQJjiy","session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"747506bc-0626-4c40-9160-7d65f060d1f9"}
