{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VEgvFULS4MAv3HyuE6g2iv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2022.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.concurrent.ArrayBlockingQueue;\n    19→\n    20→public class Diagnostics {\n    21→\tprivate static final int DRIVE_MEMORY = Integer.getInteger(\"DRIVE_MEMORY\", 0);\n    22→\tprivate static final int DRIVE_LATENCY = Integer.getInteger(\"DRIVE_LATENCY\", 0);\n    23→\tprivate static final int DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION = Integer.getInteger(\"DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION\", 0);\n    24→\tprivate static final ArrayBlockingQueue<byte[]> accumulation;\n    25→\n    26→\tstatic {\n    27→\t\tif (DRIVE_MEMORY > 0) {\n    28→\t\t\tLog.warning(\"DRIVE_MEMORY=\" + DRIVE_MEMORY\n    29→\t\t\t\t\t+ \" has been specified which will allocate that many bytes on some app requests\");\n    30→\t\t}\n    31→\t\tif (DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION > 0) {\n    32→\t\t\tLog.warning(\"DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION=\" + DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION\n    33→\t\t\t\t\t+ \" has been specified which will accumulate up to \" + (DRIVE_MEMORY * DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION)\n    34→\t\t\t\t\t+ \" bytes\");\n    35→\t\t\taccumulation = new ArrayBlockingQueue<byte[]>(DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION);\n    36→\t\t} else {\n    37→\t\t\taccumulation = null;\n    38→\t\t}\n    39→\t\tif (DRIVE_LATENCY > 0) {\n    40→\t\t\tLog.warning(\"DRIVE_LATENCY=\" + DRIVE_LATENCY\n    41→\t\t\t\t\t+ \" has been specified which will sleep that many milliseconds on some app requests\");\n    42→\t\t}\n    43→\t}\n    44→\n    45→\tpublic static void checkDiagnostics() {\n    46→\t\tif (DRIVE_MEMORY > 0) {\n    47→\t\t\tbyte[] memory = new byte[DRIVE_MEMORY];\n    48→\t\t\t// Not sure if Java will optimize this away if we don't use it, so just\n    49→\t\t\t// do something trivial\n    50→\t\t\tint count = 0;\n    51→\t\t\tfor (byte b : memory) {\n    52→\t\t\t\tif ((b & 0x01) > 0) {\n    53→\t\t\t\t\tcount++;\n    54→\t\t\t\t}\n    55→\t\t\t}\n    56→\t\t\tif (count > 0) {\n    57→\t\t\t\tLog.error(\"Something that shouldn't happen\");\n    58→\t\t\t}\n    59→\t\t\tif (DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION > 0) {\n    60→\t\t\t\tsynchronized (accumulation) {\n    61→\t\t\t\t\tif (accumulation.size() >= DRIVE_MEMACCUMULATION) {\n    62→\t\t\t\t\t\taccumulation.remove();\n    63→\t\t\t\t\t}\n    64→\t\t\t\t\taccumulation.add(memory);\n    65→\t\t\t\t}\n    66→\t\t\t}\n    67→\t\t}\n    68→\n    69→\t\tif (DRIVE_LATENCY > 0) {\n    70→\t\t\ttry {\n    71→\t\t\t\tThread.sleep(DRIVE_LATENCY);\n    72→\t\t\t} catch (InterruptedException e) {\n    73→\t\t\t\te.printStackTrace();\n    74→\t\t\t}\n    75→\t\t}\n    76→\t}\n    77→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012cytam7rdytdbG3QvQJjiy","session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"11059970-0cee-4a96-8e9d-1b71199c87a0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01M7EQqcUsMjD4mSzC2s5Viy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class MDBStats extends java.util.HashMap<String, TimerStat> {\n    25→\n    26→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -3759835921094193760L;\n    27→    // Singleton class\n    28→    private static MDBStats mdbStats = null;\n    29→\n    30→    private MDBStats() {\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    public static synchronized MDBStats getInstance() {\n    34→        if (mdbStats == null) {\n    35→            mdbStats = new MDBStats();\n    36→        }\n    37→        return mdbStats;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public TimerStat addTiming(String type, long sendTime, long recvTime) {\n    41→        TimerStat stats = null;\n    42→        synchronized (type) {\n    43→\n    44→            stats = get(type);\n    45→            if (stats == null) {\n    46→                stats = new TimerStat();\n    47→            }\n    48→\n    49→            long time = recvTime - sendTime;\n    50→            if (time > stats.getMax()) {\n    51→                stats.setMax(time);\n    52→            }\n    53→            if (time < stats.getMin()) {\n    54→                stats.setMin(time);\n    55→            }\n    56→            stats.setCount(stats.getCount() + 1);\n    57→            stats.setTotalTime(stats.getTotalTime() + time);\n    58→\n    59→            put(type, stats);\n    60→        }\n    61→        return stats;\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    public synchronized void reset() {\n    65→        clear();\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012cytam7rdytdbG3QvQJjiy","session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"0660f6ca-1019-404c-ade4-894bb513ae16"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HK8WbY4RnWNpcuQHrHQukH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.AbstractSequentialList;\n    19→import java.util.ListIterator;\n    20→\n    21→public class KeyBlock extends AbstractSequentialList<Object> {\n    22→\n    23→    // min and max provide range of valid primary keys for this KeyBlock\n    24→    private int min = 0;\n    25→    private int max = 0;\n    26→    private int index = 0;\n    27→\n    28→    /**\n    29→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    30→     */\n    31→    public KeyBlock() {\n    32→        super();\n    33→        min = 0;\n    34→        max = 0;\n    35→        index = min;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Constructor for KeyBlock\n    40→     */\n    41→    public KeyBlock(int min, int max) {\n    42→        super();\n    43→        this.min = min;\n    44→        this.max = max;\n    45→        index = min;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    /**\n    49→     * @see AbstractCollection#size()\n    50→     */\n    51→    @Override\n    52→    public int size() {\n    53→        return (max - min) + 1;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * @see AbstractSequentialList#listIterator(int)\n    58→     */\n    59→    @Override\n    60→    public ListIterator<Object> listIterator(int arg0) {\n    61→        return new KeyBlockIterator();\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    class KeyBlockIterator implements ListIterator<Object> {\n    65→\n    66→        /**\n    67→         * @see ListIterator#hasNext()\n    68→         */\n    69→        @Override\n    70→        public boolean hasNext() {\n    71→            return index <= max;\n    72→        }\n    73→\n    74→        /**\n    75→         * @see ListIterator#next()\n    76→         */\n    77→        @Override\n    78→        public synchronized Object next() {\n    79→            if (index > max) {\n    80→                throw new java.lang.RuntimeException(\"KeyBlock:next() -- Error KeyBlock depleted\");\n    81→            }\n    82→            return new Integer(index++);\n    83→        }\n    84→\n    85→        /**\n    86→         * @see ListIterator#hasPrevious()\n    87→         */\n    88→        @Override\n    89→        public boolean hasPrevious() {\n    90→            return index > min;\n    91→        }\n    92→\n    93→        /**\n    94→         * @see ListIterator#previous()\n    95→         */\n    96→        @Override\n    97→        public Object previous() {\n    98→            return new Integer(--index);\n    99→        }\n   100→\n   101→        /**\n   102→         * @see ListIterator#nextIndex()\n   103→         */\n   104→        @Override\n   105→        public int nextIndex() {\n   106→            return index - min;\n   107→        }\n   108→\n   109→        /**\n   110→         * @see ListIterator#previousIndex()\n   111→         */\n   112→        @Override\n   113→        public int previousIndex() {\n   114→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: previousIndex() not supported\");\n   115→        }\n   116→\n   117→        /**\n   118→         * @see ListIterator#add()\n   119→         */\n   120→        @Override\n   121→        public void add(Object o) {\n   122→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: add() not supported\");\n   123→        }\n   124→\n   125→        /**\n   126→         * @see ListIterator#remove()\n   127→         */\n   128→        @Override\n   129→        public void remove() {\n   130→            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"KeyBlock: remove() not supported\");\n   131→        }\n   132→\n   133→        /**\n   134→         * @see ListIterator#set(Object)\n   135→         */\n   136→        @Override\n   137→        public void set(Object arg0) {\n   138→        }\n   139→    }\n   140→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012cytam7rdytdbG3QvQJjiy","session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"6a005be9-74d3-4c64-bca7-05045d38a4d3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01C5zqdxX1kjpFW2QaeptpgC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ *\n    20→ * To change this generated comment edit the template variable \"typecomment\":\n    21→ * Window>Preferences>Java>Templates. To enable and disable the creation of type\n    22→ * comments go to Window>Preferences>Java>Code Generation.\n    23→ */\n    24→public class TimerStat {\n    25→\n    26→    private double min = 1000000000.0, max = 0.0, totalTime = 0.0;\n    27→    private int count;\n    28→\n    29→    /**\n    30→     * Returns the count.\n    31→     *\n    32→     * @return int\n    33→     */\n    34→    public int getCount() {\n    35→        return count;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    /**\n    39→     * Returns the max.\n    40→     *\n    41→     * @return double\n    42→     */\n    43→    public double getMax() {\n    44→        return max;\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    /**\n    48→     * Returns the min.\n    49→     *\n    50→     * @return double\n    51→     */\n    52→    public double getMin() {\n    53→        return min;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    /**\n    57→     * Sets the count.\n    58→     *\n    59→     * @param count\n    60→     *            The count to set\n    61→     */\n    62→    public void setCount(int count) {\n    63→        this.count = count;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    /**\n    67→     * Sets the max.\n    68→     *\n    69→     * @param max\n    70→     *            The max to set\n    71→     */\n    72→    public void setMax(double max) {\n    73→        this.max = max;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    /**\n    77→     * Sets the min.\n    78→     *\n    79→     * @param min\n    80→     *            The min to set\n    81→     */\n    82→    public void setMin(double min) {\n    83→        this.min = min;\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    /**\n    87→     * Returns the totalTime.\n    88→     *\n    89→     * @return double\n    90→     */\n    91→    public double getTotalTime() {\n    92→        return totalTime;\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    /**\n    96→     * Sets the totalTime.\n    97→     *\n    98→     * @param totalTime\n    99→     *            The totalTime to set\n   100→     */\n   101→    public void setTotalTime(double totalTime) {\n   102→        this.totalTime = totalTime;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    /**\n   106→     * Returns the max in Secs\n   107→     *\n   108→     * @return double\n   109→     */\n   110→    public double getMaxSecs() {\n   111→        return max / 1000.0;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    /**\n   115→     * Returns the min in Secs\n   116→     *\n   117→     * @return double\n   118→     */\n   119→    public double getMinSecs() {\n   120→        return min / 1000.0;\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    /**\n   124→     * Returns the average time in Secs\n   125→     *\n   126→     * @return double\n   127→     */\n   128→    public double getAvgSecs() {\n   129→\n   130→        double avg = getTotalTime() / getCount();\n   131→        return avg / 1000.0;\n   132→    }\n   133→}\n   134→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012cytam7rdytdbG3QvQJjiy","session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"d84a70c3-021f-49e0-add4-adf4a12af94a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UyzPv3d3grq3WeosRCDMGS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * (C) Copyright IBM Corporation 2015.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→ * you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→ * You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→ *\n     8→ * http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→ *\n    10→ * Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→ * distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→ * WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→ * See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→ * limitations under the License.\n    15→ */\n    16→package com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.entities;\n    17→\n    18→import java.io.Serializable;\n    19→import java.math.BigDecimal;\n    20→import java.sql.Timestamp;\n    21→import java.util.Collection;\n    22→import java.util.Date;\n    23→\n    24→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    25→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    27→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    28→import jakarta.persistence.GenerationType;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    32→import jakarta.persistence.OneToOne;\n    33→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    34→import jakarta.persistence.TableGenerator;\n    35→import jakarta.persistence.Temporal;\n    36→import jakarta.persistence.TemporalType;\n    37→import jakarta.persistence.Transient;\n    38→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    39→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PastOrPresent;\n    40→import jakarta.validation.constraints.PositiveOrZero;\n    41→\n    42→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.Log;\n    43→import com.ibm.websphere.samples.daytrader.util.TradeConfig;\n    44→\n    45→@Entity(name = \"accountejb\")\n    46→@Table(name = \"accountejb\")\n    47→public class AccountDataBean implements Serializable {\n    48→\n    49→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 8437841265136840545L;\n    50→\n    51→    /* Accessor methods for persistent fields */\n    52→    @TableGenerator(name = \"accountIdGen\", table = \"KEYGENEJB\", pkColumnName = \"KEYNAME\", valueColumnName = \"KEYVAL\", pkColumnValue = \"account\", allocationSize = 1000)\n    53→    @Id\n    54→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.TABLE, generator = \"accountIdGen\")\n    55→    @Column(name = \"ACCOUNTID\", nullable = false)\n    56→    private Integer accountID; /* accountID */\n    57→\n    58→    @NotNull\n    59→    @PositiveOrZero\n    60→    @Column(name = \"LOGINCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    61→    private int loginCount; /* loginCount */\n    62→\n    63→    @NotNull\n    64→    @PositiveOrZero\n    65→    @Column(name = \"LOGOUTCOUNT\", nullable = false)\n    66→    private int logoutCount; /* logoutCount */\n    67→\n    68→    @Column(name = \"LASTLOGIN\")\n    69→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    70→    @PastOrPresent\n    71→    private Date lastLogin; /* lastLogin Date */\n    72→\n    73→    @Column(name = \"CREATIONDATE\")\n    74→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    75→    @PastOrPresent\n    76→    private Date creationDate; /* creationDate */\n    77→\n    78→    @Column(name = \"BALANCE\")\n    79→    private BigDecimal balance; /* balance */\n    80→\n    81→    @Column(name = \"OPENBALANCE\")\n    82→    private BigDecimal openBalance; /* open balance */\n    83→\n    84→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    85→    private Collection<OrderDataBean> orders;\n    86→\n    87→    @OneToMany(mappedBy = \"account\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    88→    private Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings;\n    89→\n    90→    @OneToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    91→    @JoinColumn(name = \"PROFILE_USERID\")\n    92→    private AccountProfileDataBean profile;\n    93→\n    94→    /*\n    95→     * Accessor methods for relationship fields are only included for the\n    96→     * AccountProfile profileID\n    97→     */\n    98→    @Transient\n    99→    private String profileID;\n   100→\n   101→    public AccountDataBean() {\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    public AccountDataBean(Integer accountID, int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate, BigDecimal balance, BigDecimal openBalance,\n   105→            String profileID) {\n   106→        setAccountID(accountID);\n   107→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n   108→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n   109→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n   110→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n   111→        setBalance(balance);\n   112→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   113→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→    public AccountDataBean(int loginCount, int logoutCount, Date lastLogin, Date creationDate, BigDecimal balance, BigDecimal openBalance, String profileID) {\n   117→        setLoginCount(loginCount);\n   118→        setLogoutCount(logoutCount);\n   119→        setLastLogin(lastLogin);\n   120→        setCreationDate(creationDate);\n   121→        setBalance(balance);\n   122→        setOpenBalance(openBalance);\n   123→        setProfileID(profileID);\n   124→    }\n   125→\n   126→    public static AccountDataBean getRandomInstance() {\n   127→        return new AccountDataBean(new Integer(TradeConfig.rndInt(100000)), // accountID\n   128→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // loginCount\n   129→                TradeConfig.rndInt(10000), // logoutCount\n   130→                new java.util.Date(), // lastLogin\n   131→                new java.util.Date(TradeConfig.rndInt(Integer.MAX_VALUE)), // creationDate\n   132→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // balance\n   133→                TradeConfig.rndBigDecimal(1000000.0f), // openBalance\n   134→                TradeConfig.rndUserID() // profileID\n   135→        );\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    @Override\n   139→    public String toString() {\n   140→        return \"\\n\\tAccount Data for account: \" + getAccountID() + \"\\n\\t\\t   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount() + \"\\n\\t\\t  logoutCount:\" + getLogoutCount()\n   141→                + \"\\n\\t\\t    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"\\n\\t\\t creationDate:\" + getCreationDate() + \"\\n\\t\\t      balance:\" + getBalance()\n   142→                + \"\\n\\t\\t  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"\\n\\t\\t    profileID:\" + getProfileID();\n   143→    }\n   144→\n   145→    public String toHTML() {\n   146→        return \"<BR>Account Data for account: <B>\" + getAccountID() + \"</B>\" + \"<LI>   loginCount:\" + getLoginCount() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  logoutCount:\"\n   147→                + getLogoutCount() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    lastLogin:\" + getLastLogin() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI> creationDate:\" + getCreationDate() + \"</LI>\"\n   148→                + \"<LI>      balance:\" + getBalance() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>  openBalance:\" + getOpenBalance() + \"</LI>\" + \"<LI>    profileID:\" + getProfileID()\n   149→                + \"</LI>\";\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    public void print() {\n   153→        Log.log(this.toString());\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    public Integer getAccountID() {\n   157→        return accountID;\n   158→    }\n   159→\n   160→    public void setAccountID(Integer accountID) {\n   161→        this.accountID = accountID;\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    public int getLoginCount() {\n   165→        return loginCount;\n   166→    }\n   167→\n   168→    public void setLoginCount(int loginCount) {\n   169→        this.loginCount = loginCount;\n   170→    }\n   171→\n   172→    public int getLogoutCount() {\n   173→        return logoutCount;\n   174→    }\n   175→\n   176→    public void setLogoutCount(int logoutCount) {\n   177→        this.logoutCount = logoutCount;\n   178→    }\n   179→\n   180→    public Date getLastLogin() {\n   181→        return lastLogin;\n   182→    }\n   183→\n   184→    public void setLastLogin(Date lastLogin) {\n   185→        this.lastLogin = lastLogin;\n   186→    }\n   187→\n   188→    public Date getCreationDate() {\n   189→        return creationDate;\n   190→    }\n   191→\n   192→    public void setCreationDate(Date creationDate) {\n   193→        this.creationDate = creationDate;\n   194→    }\n   195→\n   196→    public BigDecimal getBalance() {\n   197→        return balance;\n   198→    }\n   199→\n   200→    public void setBalance(BigDecimal balance) {\n   201→        this.balance = balance;\n   202→    }\n   203→\n   204→    public BigDecimal getOpenBalance() {\n   205→        return openBalance;\n   206→    }\n   207→\n   208→    public void setOpenBalance(BigDecimal openBalance) {\n   209→        this.openBalance = openBalance;\n   210→    }\n   211→\n   212→    public String getProfileID() {\n   213→        return profileID;\n   214→    }\n   215→\n   216→    public void setProfileID(String profileID) {\n   217→        this.profileID = profileID;\n   218→    }\n   219→\n   220→    /*\n   221→     * Disabled for D185273 public String getUserID() { return getProfileID(); }\n   222→     */\n   223→\n   224→    public Collection<OrderDataBean> getOrders() {\n   225→        return orders;\n   226→    }\n   227→\n   228→    public void setOrders(Collection<OrderDataBean> orders) {\n   229→        this.orders = orders;\n   230→    }\n   231→\n   232→    public Collection<HoldingDataBean> getHoldings() {\n   233→        return holdings;\n   234→    }\n   235→\n   236→    public void setHoldings(Collection<HoldingDataBean> holdings) {\n   237→        this.holdings = holdings;\n   238→    }\n   239→\n   240→    public AccountProfileDataBean getProfile() {\n   241→        return profile;\n   242→    }\n   243→\n   244→    public void setProfile(AccountProfileDataBean profile) {\n   245→        this.profile = profile;\n   246→    }\n   247→\n   248→    public void login(String password) {\n   249→        AccountProfileDataBean profile = getProfile();\n   250→        if ((profile == null) || (profile.getPassword().equals(password) == false)) {\n   251→            String error = \"AccountBean:Login failure for account: \" + getAccountID()\n   252→                    + ((profile == null) ? \"null AccountProfile\" : \"\\n\\tIncorrect password-->\" + profile.getUserID() + \":\" + profile.getPassword());\n   253→            throw new RuntimeException(error);\n   254→        }\n   255→\n   256→        setLastLogin(new Timestamp(System.currentTimeMillis()));\n   257→        setLoginCount(getLoginCount() + 1);\n   258→    }\n   259→\n   260→    public void logout() {\n   261→        setLogoutCount(getLogoutCount() + 1);\n   262→    }\n   263→\n   264→    @Override\n   265→    public int hashCode() {\n   266→        int hash = 0;\n   267→        hash += (this.accountID != null ? this.accountID.hashCode() : 0);\n   268→        return hash;\n   269→    }\n   270→\n   271→    @Override\n   272→    public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   273→        \n   274→        if (!(object instanceof AccountDataBean)) {\n   275→            return false;\n   276→        }\n   277→        AccountDataBean other = (AccountDataBean) object;\n   278→\n   279→        if (this.accountID != other.accountID && (this.accountID == null || !this.accountID.equals(other.accountID))) {\n   280→            return false;\n   281→        }\n   282→\n   283→        return true;\n   284→    }\n   285→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012cytam7rdytdbG3QvQJjiy","session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"9b051040-959c-4a63-b8a3-aeb42331e0bd"}
