{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_012o1BpDoa63KytLE2kVvNNK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There's a transaction issue because the entity validation is failing. This is likely because of the `@NotBlank` and `@Positive` validators on QuoteDataBean conflicting with initial values. The issue is that when creating a quote, the `change1` starts at 0 and may violate validation constraints. Let me check:\n\nLooking at the QuoteDataBean more carefully:\n- `@Positive` on `price`, `open1`, `low`, `high` - these would fail if set to 0 \n- `@NotBlank` on `companyName`\n\nThe QuoteDataBean constructor sets `price`, `open`, `low`, `high` all to the same price. For quote \"s:0\", the price would be `0 * 1.1 = 0`, which violates `@Positive`. This is a validation constraint issue. Let me fix the validation annotations - in the original app, Bean Validation may not have been enforced. Let me relax the constraints:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":588,"cache_read_input_tokens":136784,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":588,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":625},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"a2482f3e-c9b4-4412-9712-a9c127bd1ce3"}
