{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Wv6Yo64YnDVFmjqWUMwQRr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two issues:\n\n1. **Account Page (500)** - `LazyInitializationException` - The `AccountDataBean.orders` collection has `LAZY` fetch and the Hibernate session is closed when the JSP tries to access it. I need to either make the fetch EAGER or use `@Transactional` more broadly.\n\n2. **Scenario Servlet (500)** - `No such user: uid:33` - The database isn't populated with test users (uid:0 through uid:199). This is expected since we don't have the buildDB functionality. The scenario servlet tries to work with pre-populated users.\n\nLet me fix the LazyInitializationException by enabling `spring.jpa.open-in-view=true` (already default) and also by eagerly loading orders in the account data retrieval method:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1515,"cache_read_input_tokens":121555,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1515,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":355},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"026a30f8-27d7-4b4c-9adf-eefe172c4b7d"}
