{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BJ5ufTmmVUi9jqbFq7UzgL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is that the `account.jsp` template calls `.size()` on the orders collection. Even though I added eager initialization in `getAccountData()`, the problem is that `@Transactional` boundaries on the service don't extend to the JSP rendering. The open-in-view filter should handle this but the servlets are using `@WebServlet` which bypasses Spring's DispatcherServlet.\n\nThe real fix is to either:\n1. Change fetch type to EAGER on the entity\n2. Or ensure the `open-in-view` interceptor applies to servlet requests\n\nSince servlets registered via `@WebServlet`/`@ServletComponentScan` bypass Spring's OpenEntityManagerInViewInterceptor, I need to change the entity fetch type:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1154,"cache_read_input_tokens":127695,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1154,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":470},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc03748e-8f3c-4e9b-a627-5ed371f2cf3e","uuid":"d7d140c3-9059-4d38-bd78-d4252d21b289"}
